title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Beat cake mix, oil and eggs well.
Add the undrained oranges. Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Combine jello and boiling water.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: all-in-one
directions: Combine all ingredients, including liquids in cans, in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with shredded cheese and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serves 15.
Can be prepared a day ahead but reduce cooking time.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole dish.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and milk well.
Cover margarine with this mixture evenly. Put peaches with juice and 1/2 cup of sugar on top of this. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: soup-er chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in oblong baking dish. Arrange chicken pieces in dish and pour rice over chicken. Mix all soups together. Pour evenly over rice. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yummy yogurt pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into graham cracker crust. Garnish with strawberries.
Chill.

title: pizza popcorn
directions: Combine butter, garlic salt, salt and oregano in small saucepan.
Stir over low heat until butter melts.
Pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Spread in shallow pan or cookie sheet and sprinkle cheese over all.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook apples and put through a colander to make apple pulp. Place 10 cups of pulp in crock-pot with remaining ingredients. Turn on high and cover.
Stir occasionally.
As butter cooks down, add remaining pulp.
(If pot is large enough, put in all the pulp at the start.)
Turn temperature to low and allow to cook overnight.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Place cucumbers and 1 pint salt in 3 quarts boiling water.
Let stand 1 week.
Drain; cover with boiling water and let stand 24 hours.
Drain.
Add alum; cover with boiling water and let stand 24 hours.
Add celery seed, vinegar, dill and 3 cups sugar and let stand without heating for 24 hours.
Keep this syrup when draining. Add 2 cups sugar and let stand 24 hours.
Drain syrup; bring to boil, add 3 cups sugar and let stand 24 hours.
Drain syrup; bring to boil, add 4 cups sugar and let stand 24 hours.
Bring to boil and can.
Add the cucumbers to each step.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until cheese melts, stirring often.
To serve, transfer dip to a chafing dish.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Makes approximately 6 cups.

title: cauliflower & broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain one head cauliflower and one bunch broccoli. Cut into small pieces. Add 16 oz. can drained tiny peas and one cup grated Cheddar cheese.

title: black-eyed peas with rice
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet; remove.
Reserve drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onion in drippings until tender.
Drain onion; discard drippings.
Return onion to skillet.
Add peas and last 5 ingredients.
Cook over low heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Spoon into serving dish and crumble bacon over top.

title: quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie crusts and cook at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes approximately.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Coarsely slice cabbage.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Slightly brown meat with onions; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over cabbage.
In a bowl mix together rice, sugar, tomatoes and catsup.
Pour over meat and cabbage.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quickie stroganoff
directions: Cook
in
skillet,
brown
beef cubes, salt and pepper. Put cans
of soup, right from can, no water.
Stir in 1/2 sour cream. Simmer.
Cook noodles.
Serve sauce over noodles.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat together eggs, lemon juice and milk; add to butter mixture.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt, then add to mixture. Stir in poppy seed and lemon rind.
Pour batter 2/3 full into 12 greased muffin cups (about 26 mini-muffins).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (10 to 15 for mini-muffins).
Cool.

title: dang good pie
directions: Mix ingredients well by hand.
Pour into a 9-inch uncooked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
May take 1 hour to cook.

title: easy crab appetizers
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add crab and sprinkling of garlic powder.
Stir.
Place in freezer for about 15 minutes.
When spreadable, spread over English muffin halves.
Cut into quarters.
Place on large cookie sheet and freeze, uncovered.
Once frozen, place in bags and keep frozen until ready to use.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden and bubbly.

title: hot cornbread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in large mixing bowl, stir together.
Add the eggs and mix well.
One at a time, add the other ingredients, mixing well after each. Pour into cake pan and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: soft-frozen lemonade
directions: Cut and squeeze lemons.
Remove seeds but leave some of the pulp.
You should have about 3 cups of juice.
Pour juice into a gallon-sized glass beverage container.
Heat 1 cup water to boiling.
Add sugar and stir until sugar dissolves.
Add to lemon juice and add enough water to make full gallon.
Stir well.
Place in freezer and check after about 3 hours.
Stir to keep lemonade from freezing solid.
Stir often to form a slush, scraping ice from sides of jar.

title: curried chicken for 8
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in butter. Stir in flour. Gradually blend in

chicken broth, salt, pepper, curry and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until sauce is thick. Stir occasionally. Add chicken. Serve over rice with condiments of coconut and peanuts. May cut recipe in half or freeze half and serve 4.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add to mixture.
Fold flour, vanilla, buttermilk and salt into mixture.
Mix vinegar and soda together and fold into batter.
Beat as you would any other cake.
Bake at 350° in two 9-inch round pans for 30 to 35 minutes (or as a sheet cake).

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Do not use metal spoon!

title: cherry fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chocolate chip reese's cookies
directions: Double this recipe except use only 1 bag of mini chips.
Mix together the butter, brown sugar, sugar and eggs.
Add the vanilla, soda and flour.
Mix well.
Add the chips.
Mix well. Put mini muffin papers in mini muffin pans.
Scoop about 1/2 teaspoon of dough and put in each paper.
Bake about 9 to 11 minutes.
While baking, open Reese's peanut butter cups so you can insert them inside of cookie as soon as they come out of the oven. Doubled recipe makes about 120 cookies.
Let cool.
Bake at 375°.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Cook sausage and drain well.
Place bread, cheese and sausage in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour milk and egg mixture over ingredients. Refrigerate until next day, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes and serve.

title: cream cheese muffin puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and almond extract.
In another small bowl, combine margarine and vanilla.

title: broccoli chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish and cook at 350° until almost done.
Add soup and water chestnuts, then sprinkle on cheese and onion rings last.
Return to oven and cook until all the mixture bubbles.

title: pound cake #2
directions: Separate eggs.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar together. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Add dry ingredients alternating with the milk and extracts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine margarine and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each. Then add flour and milk, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and cocoa.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into lined and greased tube pan.
Bake for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: minty mallows
directions: Combine over hot, not boiling, water, chocolate mint morsels and sweetened condensed milk.
Stir until smooth.

title: mincemeat drop cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Partially cook bacon; cut in 1/2.
Wrap around row of scallops, chicken livers or bite-size franks.
Broil until bacon is crispy.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk and stir in sugar, salt and margarine. Soften yeast in water.
Add milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead 5 minutes. Let rise 30 minutes.
Punch down.
Shape rolls onto greased pan. Cover.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 400°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: german slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and sugar; let stand 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cool.
Will keep several days in the refrigerator.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix.
Pour into greased and floured tube or bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: mom's sugarless apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice thin the apples into a bowl.
Mix juice, cornstarch and cinnamon and pour over sliced apples.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cortland's cherry pie
directions: Cook 7 minutes until thick.
Bake in a 9-inch pie plate in an unbaked shell with topping at 425° for 10 minutes.
Lower oven to 350°.
Cook another 35 minutes.

title: curried fruit
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and curry and stir to dissolve. Drain fruits and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour sugar mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: glazed carrots(low calorie)
directions: Add all ingredients in a nonstick skillet.
Heat until bubbly. Add carrots and simmer until tender-crisp (about 5 minutes for frozen carrots).

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onion in margarine; heat for 3 to 5 minutes. Sprinkle salt, pepper and flour over shrimp mixture.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not boil.
Serve over rice.

title: minnesota wild rice soup
directions: In a heavy, at least 4-quart soup kettle, brown the beef with the salt and Italian seasoning, crumbling the meat as it cooks. Add the wild rice, water, Tabasco sauce, bouillon granules, pepper, celery and onion; simmer about 60 minutes, until rice splits.
Stir in the soup and soup cans of water.
Cover and simmer another 30 minutes.
Adjust seasonings, if desired.
If soup is too thick, add more water.
May substitute ground turkey.

title: "impossible" broccoli quiche
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Thaw and drain broccoli.
Spread broccoli on bottom of pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese and onion. Place milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper in blender.
Whirl for 15 seconds.
Pour over contents of pie plate.
Put in preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Test for doneness with knife.

title: classic waldorf salad
directions: Pour the pineapple with its juice into a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until juice comes to a boil, about 4 to 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour gelatin mix into large, glass mixing bowl.
Carefully pour pineapple and juice into bowl.
Stir with a wooden spoon until gelatin is dissolved.
Chill in the refrigerator until it is cool and begins to thicken, about 2 hours.

title: water cookies
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Sift the next 4 ingredients.
Mix dry mixture with cream mixture.
Add apples and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After 1 hour, turn oven off. Let cake remain 5 minutes longer.
Remove from oven; let cake cool in pan.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add seasonings.
Spread meat mixture on slices of bread.
Place on cookie sheets.
Top with cheese.
Place in oven 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: korean garlic steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except soy sauce.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator or 4 hours room temperature.
Add soy sauce a few minutes before broiling.
Broil for 3 minutes on each side, basting with remaining liquid.
Slice diagonally.

title: blue whale(alcoholic drink)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shake and pour into a tall glass.

title: fruit nog pie
directions: Drain fruit cocktail well; measure 1/2 cup of the syrup.
Stir gelatine into syrup, set over boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat; stir in egg nog.
Add salt and flavorings.
Chill until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon. Whip the whipped cream.
Fold into gelatine mixture with 1 1/2 cups fruit cocktail.
Chill again.
Heap mixture into pie shell. Chill 2 to 4 hours.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook beets. Cut into thin slices or cubes.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and vinegar in a saucepan.
Let sauce boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add butter and pour over beets. Let stand to absorb the flavor.

title: oysters rockefeller i
directions: Saute onion, celery and herbs in 4 tablespoons of the butter for 3 minutes.
Add the watercress and let it just wilt, about 2 minutes.
Put this mixture with the rest of th butter, the bread crumbs, the clam juice and anise extract into the blender.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and pinch of cayenne.
Blend for 1 minute.
Put about 1 tablespoon of this on each oyster, place the oysters on beds of rock salt in individual containers of in pie pans and dampen the salt slightly.
Bake at 450° to 475° for about 4 minutes or until the butter is melted and the oysters heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until mixture forms soft ball, when tested in cold water.
When this happens, turn off heat, add imitation vanilla and let stay on stove for a few minutes, until mixture stops bubbling.
Remove from stove. Add peanut butter and nuts.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered platter.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Saute onions in margarine until transparent, set aside to cool. Cook Minute rice as directed on box and set aside to cool. Carefully break leaves from cabbage head so as to keep leaves from tearing.
Wash leaves.
Drop leaves in boiling water just long enough to make pliable.
In large bowl, mix together pork, beef, onion, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape mixture into 8 oval "loaves."
Wrap each loaf with a cabbage leaf and place in 8 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Squeeze tomatoes and juice over each loaf. Stick in bay leaves.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate banana bobs
directions: Prepare fruits such as apples, apricots, figs, peaches, pear and prunes as directed on package.
Or soak in cold water until plump; simmer in same water in covered saucepan 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.
Sweeten to taste.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice. Whip Avoset with 4 teaspoons sugar, then fold into cheese mixture. Pour into baked crust.
Put Cool Whip on top or 1 can blueberry pie mix.

title: tex-mex layered dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Put in layers on platter:
Spread bean dip; top with avocado mixture. Top with sour cream mixture; sprinkle onions, tomatoes and olives. Cover with cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: carrot ring
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into well greased ring mold.
Set mold in a shallow pan of water and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm.
Remove from oven.
Let stand for a few minutes, loosen edges and turn out carefully.
Fill center with green peas.

title: beans, beans and more beans(great for the crock-pot)
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Drain beans, except the pork and beans.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix together to make batter.
Dip 2 tablespoons on buttered grill and cook until brown.

title: daddy's special cooked rice
directions: Bring cream, water, sugar and butter to a boil.
Lower heat and add instant rice.
Set to rice fluffs.
Serve in small bowls for breakfast.

title: peach treat
directions: Melt margarine in a deep dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk together.
Pour this batter over margarine. Do not mix.
Add 1 cup sugar to drained peaches.
Pour on top of batter and bake 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: cranberry pear compote
directions: Boil sugar, water and lemon juice together 5 minutes.
Core and chop pears.
Add to mixture.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add cranberries and simmer 7 minutes.
Add lemon rind, cinnamon and allspice to mixture in pan.
Cool.
Add to it more lemon juice.
Makes 6 cups. Freezes well.
Delicious served with main dish as garnish/side dish.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir together cornmeal, flour, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add beaten egg and melted margarine.
Stir until mixed and then add to dry ingredients and mix well. Turn into greased 9 x 9-inch pan or into greased muffin pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden and done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix margarine, cheese and pepper.
Add flour and Rice Krispies.
Mix well and roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine egg whites, milk and oil. Add dry ingredients; do not beat.
Stir just enough to mix.
Add some raisins and drained crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Bake at 425° for 18 minutes.
Vary with other fruits such as blueberries, peaches, bananas, prunes and some molasses, etc.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook Stove Top stuffing as directed on box.
In greased baking dish, layer dressing, then chicken, ending up with dressing.
Mix soups together and pour over layers. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Place the sour cream, pepper, mustard, salt, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl; blend for 2 minutes at low speed. Add the mayonnaise and blend 1 1/2 minutes at low speed, then crumble the Bleu cheese by hand into small pieces.
Add to mixture, blending again at low speed no longer than 4 minutes. Allow to sit 24 hours before use.
I have blended this by hand and it is very good.
Makes 2 1/2 cups dressing.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift Bisquick. In a large mixing bowl, break up pork into chunks; gradually add in Bisquick, cheese and crushed red pepper. Mix well. With hands, roll into quarter sized balls and place on a cookie sheet. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hershey's microwave mousse
directions: Melt hershey bar in microwave on low, stirring constantly. Mix in marshmallow creme.
Stir in cool whip until well blended. Chill and serve.

title: polish vegetable soup
directions: Boil the first six ingredients for 15 minutes, then add potatoes and cauliflower.
Simmer this until all vegetables are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt together candy bars and oleo and cool.

title: molasses candy
directions: Cook until hard ball.
Pour on a buttered dish.
Work edges in until cool enough to pull.
Grease hands and pull until it becomes white or light brown in color, then break into pieces and serve. Becomes very hard when cooled.

title: chocolate biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits, sprinkle them with sugar and enough milk to soften; set aside.
Blend the eggs, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Add biscuit mixture.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into large baking dish.
Cover with meringue.
Bake until light brown at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Wash head of cauliflower; break into florets.
Parboil 10 to 15 minutes in salted water until tender.
Do not cook completely. Drain and chill.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Combine fruit and nuts in a large bowl.
In another bowl, mix eggs, sugar and dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour creamed mixture over fruit.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan or loaf pans or cupcake papers.
Bake in 300° oven 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Cool in pan.
Remove and wrap.
Soak in fruit juice or wine.
Store in refrigerator.

title: b.l.t.'s
directions: Chop raw bacon into small pieces.
Cook until crisp.
Drain well.
Mix with Miracle Whip to taste.

title: brown basic dough cookies
directions: Mix Crisco with sugars; beat well with eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Throw in semi-sweet chocolate chips, M&M's, maraschino cherries, whatever type of flavored ingredient you choose.
Roll into balls the size of walnut.
Place on greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until bottoms only are golden brown.
Best if slightly underbaked.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight before serving.
Serve with a variety of chips and/or crackers.

title: frosting for whoopie pies
directions: Beat together until fluffy.

title: energy bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, wheat germ and baking soda.
Set aside.
In blender, combine eggs, banana, honey, water and vanilla.
Pour over dry ingredients; stir in the walnuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes. Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: lib's cornbread salad
directions: Bake an 8 or 9-inch skillet of cornbread.
When cool, crumble up and reserve 1 cup for the top.
Brown sausage and drain well. Pour boiling water over sausage and drain again.
Chop bread and butter pickles, onion, tomatoes and pepper.
Combine crumbled cornbread, chopped vegetables and sausage.
Toss well.
Add mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Mix well.
Garnish with 1 cup cornbread and chopped peppers.
Store in refrigerator.

title: peanut crust
directions: Combine nuts, butter and sugar.
Press evenly into bottom and on sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool and fill.

title: mom's 1-pot dinner
directions: Pour the beans into a large Dutch oven.
Add potatoes and sausage and cook over low heat until potatoes are tender.
Long simmering only improves the flavor.

title: rotel chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add chicken and soups.
Melt Velveeta and Rotel in microwave.
Add to spaghetti and chicken. Place in casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for about 30 to 45 minutes (or until bubbly).

title: chicken briyani
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and debone.
Use chicken bones to make stock and strain.
Wash and drain rice.
Soak chicken in yogurt for about 45 minutes.
Soak saffron in a little hot water for 10 minutes.
Fry cumin without oil and pound finely.

title: delicious orange cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients with milk alternately.
Add orange juice and rind.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit spread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat until smooth.
Stir in fruit. Serve on bread.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour or line with paper baking cups (30 muffin cups); fill 2/3 full.

title: meat loaf
directions: In small bowl, mix everything but meat.
Add meat to mixture in large bowl.
Bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: grape-nuts pudding(garret's delight!)
directions: You will also need 1 yard of pretty ribbon.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together.
Mix into a loaf.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Slice off in 1/4-inch strip and bake in moderate oven.

title: mexican corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomatoes.
Cover and cook over moderate heat 7 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cook 2 minutes, uncovered, or until tomatoes are heated thoroughly.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Boil the chicken and remove the meat.
Put meat in a baking dish and add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix 1/4 cup melted butter with all ingredients.
Remaining 1/4 cup of butter combine with 2 cups corn flakes.
Mix well and top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: saltine candy cookies
directions: Very easy to make, takes 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in 3 x 13-inch casserole dish. Drizzle oleo and top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Pinch cake in small pieces and place in bottom of dish.
With mixer, combine sugar, cream cheese and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over cake pieces and top with cherry pie filling.

title: roman stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, separate stems.
Chop stems, onion and garlic.
Saute stems, onion and garlic until light brown.
Brown meat and drain.
Add parsley, stems, onion and garlic until all brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Stuff caps.
Place in an oiled baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
In a small casserole dish or square baking pan, bake at 350 for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: ten minute fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in 3-quart stack cooker. Add milk and butter. DO NOT STIR. Microwave at 100% power for 2 minutes. Stir well. Add vanilla and nuts. Stir until well blended. Pour into buttered medium shallow pan. Refrigerate until set. Cut into squares.

title: crab cakes
directions: Clean crab meat.
Put lemon juice over mix and then add rest of ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Beat 2 raw eggs.
Dip crab balls into cracker meal, then into egg mixture and then back into cracker meal.
Deep fry or put crab balls into crab shaped foil shells. Top with crumbs.
Dot with butter and broil until crumbs brown.

title: strawberry milkshake(lo-cal)
directions: Pour milk, sweetener and vanilla into blender.
Run blender while adding frozen strawberries one at a time.
Continue to blend for 30 seconds.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix
eggs,
oil,
pumpkin and sugar together.
Sift dry ingredients
together; then add to first mixture, mixing well. Add pineapple	and
pecan
pieces.
Pour
into
3 greased and floured loaf
pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Best if served chilled. Store in refrigerator.

title: german cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased skillet.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt kay's easy italian supper
directions: In a large skillet, over medium high heat, brown ground beef and drain.
Add vegetables and pasta.
Stir in spaghetti sauce. Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until veggies are tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Transfer to a large bowl. Sprinkle with cheese and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: choco-squares
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat.
Set aside.
Combine cake mix, butter, nuts and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Press half this mixture into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
After removing from oven, sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread caramel mixture over chips.
Crumble rest of cake mixture on top.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate 1 hour to set caramel layer.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together over boiling water.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
(May be served with whipped cream!)

title: glazed carrots
directions: Heat butter, sugar and apricot jam in saucepan or skillet, stirring to combine.
Scrape and slice carrots into desired shapes.
Cook or steam until tender-crisp.
Add carrots and salt to butter-apricot mixture in saucepan, stirring gently until carrots are evenly glazed, about 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover chicken breasts with water.
Salt lightly.
Boil until chicken breasts are cooked, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
When cooled, tear chicken breasts into bite size pieces.
Put chicken back into chicken broth.
Peel and cube potatoes, add to chicken and broth.
About 30 minutes before meal time, turn on heat
and bring to a boil for about 15 minutes (potatoes will still be slightly firm).
Mix up dumplings, according to box directions and follow box instructions for cooking.
Let stand about 5 minutes before serving.

title: 3-bean pot
directions: Fry onions in bacon fat until soft.
Mix all other ingredients.
Put all in bean pot and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Stir constantly.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high speed until foamy.
Serve right away.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until sets.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with one pie crust.
Mix all other ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put into pie crust.
Cover all with other crust.
Make slits to ventilate the top crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with green salad for a wonderful meal.

title: filling for german chocolate cake
directions: Cook over slow fire until thick, stirring constantly.
Take off and let cool.
Add 1 cup pecan meats (cut fine) and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Ice cake.

title: mrs. wyss' christmas cookies
directions: Beat the butter and sugar until light and creamy. Add flour and vanilla, mixing well after each addition.
Roll out on a well floured surface, rolling dough thin. Bake about 8 minutes in a 350° oven.
Watch!
These
brown very quickly.
If you frost these cookies, be careful, they are very fragile and break easily.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs. Then flour, baking powder, soda, salt and vanilla.
Fold in oats, corn flakes and coconut.
Bake until done.

title: jackie's apricot mist punch(50 punch cups)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir in ginger ale and ice cubes.
Just before serving, add whole frozen strawberries and lime slices to give a finishing touch.
You may add gin if you like.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add oil, sugar and zucchini. Mix well. Then add remaining ingredients. Pour into tube or rectangle pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add the eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition. Stir in lemon juice and pineapple; fold in bread cubes. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 325°
for 35 to 40 minutes, until set. Garnish with whole slices of pineapple and candied cherries.

title: dietetic fruit cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is absorbed.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: pecan chocolate tart
directions: Roll out the dough 1/8-inch thick on a lightly floured surface. Fit it into a 10-inch tart pan with a removable fluted rim and trim the edge, leaving a 1/2-inch overhang.
Fold the overhang inward onto the side of the shell, pressing it firmly, and chill the shell for 30 minutes.
Spread the chocolate, melted, on the bottom of the shell and chill the shell for 15 minutes.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
In saucepan, place the sausage, cubed Velveeta cheese, tomatoes and butter. Heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix first three ingredients thoroughly.
Mix egg, vinegar and water; pour all at once into flour mixture.
Mix well.
Roll out as usual.
This is a very easy crust to handle.
Makes 2 double crust pies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook as directed on package and drain.
Lay in bottom of casserole dish.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt oleo while stirring other ingredients together.
Add melted oleo.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Pour oleo over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Place apples and water in slow cooker. Cook on low for 10 minutes. Add sugar and spices. Continue cooking on low for 8 more hours. Remove lid from slow cooker and cook for 1 hour or until apple butter reaches desired consistency. Spoon into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring water to boil and turn off heat.
Add tea bags; place spices in a bag and add.
Cover and leave for 5 minutes.
Remove tea and spices from water.
Add sugar and juices; mix well and reheat.
Strain and serve.

title: brown sugar overnight cookies
directions: Mix and store overnight in refrigerator, then slice and bake; or use for drop cookies.

title: fruit cake
directions: Put hot water over raisins.
Mix raisins, sugar and Crisco. Mix dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to raisin mixture when cool, not cold.
Add fruit, nuts and wine.
Put into well-greased and floured pans.
Fill to 1-inch of top.
Start baking at 350° for 20 minutes, then reduce to 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring about 2 inches of oil to a high temperature in large skillet.
Put a cup of batter in a funnel and begin to release from funnel when the oil is very hot, creating a spiral pattern.
Fry until bottom is brown and flip to do other side.
Top while hot with powdered sugar.

title: creamy french dressing
directions: In a blender, whirl the oil, ketchup, garlic, vinegar, mustard, egg and wine for about 15 seconds.
Serve or pour into an airtight container and chill up to 1 week.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups; allow 1 to 2 tablespoons per serving.

title: lemon dill dip(fat-free)
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased deep pie plate.
(No crust - It makes it's own crust.) Bake on middle rack for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes one dozen.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts or raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls onto
ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
May be iced.

title: j. b.'s pool room slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, peppers and salt.
Heat to a boil in a large pot.
Add chopped vegetables and heat on low temperature (do not boil) for 20 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Add mustard and stir completely.
Pack in clean jars while hot.
Makes approximately 8 pints.

title: hunter's pie
directions: Combine vegetables and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil and cook until tender.
Drain, reserving 1 1/2 cups liquid; set vegetable and liquid aside.
Heat oil in a large skillet; add steak and cook, stirring often, until browned.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper towels; reserve 3 tablespoons drippings in skillet.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chips.
Mash into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Heat in a 300° oven until chips melt (about 5 minutes). Cool.

title: cheerio treats
directions: Place the butter and marshmallows in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 2 minutes or until puffed. Stir in the peanut butter until blended.
Add the cereal and M&M's; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 pan.
Press down gently. Cool slightly before cutting.
YIELD:
15 servings.

title: hot crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix butter, cheese, mayonnaise, garlic salt, salt and crab together in bowl, combining thoroughly.
Cut muffins into small circles using cookie cutter or jigger glass (use any shape you want for variety).
Spread mixture on muffin cutouts.
Place under broiler until bubbling.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: crab dip
directions: Put cream cheese, mayonnaise and garlic powder in blender. Blend until smooth.
Put in dish.
Add crab and mix well.
Put in serving bowl; spread seafood sauce over top.
Serve with crackers, chips, etc.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: I make my own cracker crumbs, by using rolling pin and crushing crackers not too fine.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, milk and mayonnaise to smooth dough. Divide batter evenly between 10 paper lined cupcake or muffin wells.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown. Makes 10 biscuits.
Let cool before peeling off paper.

title: chili tacos
directions: Prepare taco shells, shredded lettuce, chopped onion, tomatoes and shredded cheese (Cheddar).

title: four-bean supreme
directions: In a bowl, combine the beans.
In another bowl, combine the onion, sugars, salt lemon juice, salt, hot pepper sauce and seasonings.
Stir into beans.
Pour into a greased 2 quart baking dish.
Top with bacon pieces.
Bake
uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until heated through and bacon is crisp on top.

title: chicken and vegetable egg rolls
directions: Slice mushrooms.
Chop up chicken.
Stir-fry chicken, tofu and garlic quickly in heated cooking oil for 2 minutes.
Add vegetables; stir-fry for 30 minutes more.
Blend soy sauce into cornstarch, ginger, sugar and salt.
Stir into chicken mixture. Cook and stir until thickened.
Drop by teaspoons, about 3 or 4 , into middle of egg roll wrapper.
Egg roll wrapper is placed like diamond.
Fold top flap down the 2 sides over and bottom up and around.
Moisten edges with water; fry in oil until golden brown.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash in salt and water until done.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (until brown).

title: pepper jelly tarts(appetizer)
directions: Blend all ingredients together except jelly.
Wrap in plastic wrap and let rest overnight.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick and cut into circles.
Place about 1/4 teaspoon pepper jelly in the center of tart and fold over; crimp and seal.
These may be frozen now, or baked at 350° for about 10 minutes.
May be warmed in the microwave after they have been baked in the oven and cooled.
(I do not like this way as they seem soggy to me.)
Best to freeze for future use, then bake as needed.

title: baked chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart casserole, place uncooked noodles.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, heat oil and saute carrots, celery, onion and parsley until almost tender.
Add broth, water and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in chicken.
Pour chicken mixture over noodles; cover with crust.
Vent crust; brush lightly with milk.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, Ranch dressing and 2 cans ham together in bowl.
Form ball.
Place chopped pecans on wax paper. Roll cream cheese mixture back and forth in pecans until ball is completely covered with pecans.
Chill and serve with your choice of crackers.

title: easy caramel cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.

title: pot roast and vegetables
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven and brown meat on all sides, seasoning with salt and pepper.
Add water; cover and cook on low heat for 2 hours.
Add onions and cook 10 minutes.
Add carrots and potatoes, cooking 30 to 35 minutes longer, until tender.
Remove meat and vegetables.
Measure stock left in pot and add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Bring to boil.
Blend flour with 1/3 cup of water; stir into boiling stock, stirring until thick.
Serve over meat and vegetables.

title: broiled fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Preheat broiler.
Cut fillets into 6 portions. Place fish in a single layer in a greased baking pan. Brush half the melted butter or Dill Sauce over the fish.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Pat or cut out and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: zucchini corn muffins
directions: Grease 12-cup muffin pan; set aside.
In small bowl, combine butter, egg and milk.
In medium bowl, stir yellow cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add egg mixture, zucchini and corn, stirring until just combined.
Spoon batter into muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes or golden brown.

title: lemon crunch pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil together thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring, then the cake flour that has been sifted four times.
Add in four parts. Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
(This cake has a real crunchy top.)

title: red cucumber pickles
directions: Day 1:
Peel cucumbers, remove seeds and slice into rings. Soak in lime and enough water to cover cucumber rings.
Soak 24 hours.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch morsels in 2-quart casserole.
Heat in microwave on medium for 5 to 6 minutes or until melted.
Stir once during melting.
Stir in peanuts. Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm.

title: date cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add flour and salt; divide into fourths.
Chill 2 hours.
Work one portion and roll 1/8-inch thick on a surface dusted with powdered sugar.
Cut dough in 3 x 1-inch strips.
Place a date in center of each roll-up strip.
At 375°, bake for 15 minutes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, seam side down.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm, then again when cool.

title: date delights
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Beat eggs and sugar together. Pour into melted margarine.
Add dates and salt.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes until thick.
Mash dates as the mixture is cooking. Remove from heat, stir in cereal, nuts and vanilla.
Cool until you can handle the mixture.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut. Let stand until cooled.
Store in tins or freeze.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil and add ground beef, salt, pepper and pan drippings. In bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish, spread half of cabbage. Cover with half of meat mixture and half of the can of soup. Add some Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll into walnut size balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning. Remove from heat.
Place milk and margarine in bottom of deep baking dish. Alternate potatoes, meat, olives and grated cheese in layers.
Add salsa last. Cover and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: auburn coffee cake(serves 16)
directions: Cut shortening into flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix together egg, milk and vanilla and add to first mixture.

title: stuffed endive
directions: Core an apple to make a cup.
Stuff with cottage cheese.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix thoroughly with fork in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir and smooth in pan.
Bake at 350° until top springs back when touched, about 45 minutes.
Cool; cover and leave in pan.
Serve plain in squares.
Keeps well.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil the noodles until they are tender.
Brown hamburger, adding onions, peppers and seasonings.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, tomatoes, low-fat cottage cheese and grated Mozzarella cheese.
Top casserole with cheese.

title: walnut salad
directions: Put all ingredients into a glass bowl and mix well.
Let chill well before serving.

title: peaches and cream cheese pie
directions: Mix together flour, salt, pudding mix, butter, milk, baking powder and egg at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pie tin. Pour drained (save juice) peaches onto batter.
Mix in small bowl the cream cheese, sugar and 3 tablespoons reserved peach juice for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon to within 1 inch of edge of batter.
Mix together 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: rice dressing
directions: Prepare chicken broth by combining water and bouillon cubes; simmer.
Brown sausage and beef.
Add onion and pepper, cooking until clear.
Add simmered broth, gravy mix, sugar and garlic cloves; stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Cook down to a gravy consistency.
Remove garlic cloves; mash, then return to mixture. Combine with cooked rice.
Add onion tops and parsley prior to serving.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla espanola
directions: Peel potatoes; cut in thin slices.
Pour 1/2 cup oil in skillet.
Make sure oil is hot before adding potatoes.
Turn stove on medium-high heat.
Add potatoes, garlic, salt and onions in hot skillet.
Cover, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are done.
Potatoes are done when tender and cooked through, hot golden brown.
When done, remove potatoes from skillet.
Place potatoes on doubled paper toweling to drain excess oil.
Save about 1 to 2 teaspoons oil in skillet and discard the rest.

title: four bean salad
directions: Step 1:
Drain all the beans and pour in a large bowl.
Also, put in bell pepper and onion.
Set aside.

title: piccalilli
directions: Cut tomatoes in chunks and soak in salt water for 2 hours (1/2 cup salt and water to cover).
Cut other vegetables into bite size pieces.
Combine sugar, water, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Drain tomatoes; add vinegar mixture.
Tie cloves and cinnamon sticks in cheese cloth and add to mixture.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: lo-cal banana split cake
directions: Soften cheese by stirring.
Add milk to Ricotta and mix until blended.
(If you don't like curd, mash with potato masher.)
Add pudding mix and beat.
Will become very thick.
Spread cheese and pudding mix over cooled crust.
Slice bananas over this layer. Spread pineapple over bananas, then top with Cool Whip.

title: citrus slush
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven over high heat, bring sugar and 3 cups water to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves; remove from heat. Stir in lemonade and orange juice until melted.
Stir in pineapple juice and 3 cups cold water.
Pour into 2 (13 x 9) pans.
Cover and freeze overnight.
Place in punch bowl or individual glasses. Pour chilled pop over until slushy.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugars, salt, butter and milk in pan.
Cook until a drop forms soft (but firm) ball in cold water or until thermometer reaches 234°.
Cool until thick as syrup.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until candy thickens.
Pour into a buttered dish; cut into squares (about 36 pieces).
You can add nuts if desired.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer all ingredients in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm or cool and, if desired, with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: caramel praline brownies
directions: Melt caramels with milk, stirring often.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Blend thoroughly sugar, flour, cocoa and soda; set aside.
Mix melted butter and eggs.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients and stir just until smooth.
Spread batter into pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Carefully remove from oven and gently pour melted caramels over brownies. Sprinkle pecans over top.
Return to oven and bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes about 2 dozen 2 x 2-inch brownies.

title: hamburger and corn casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, bell pepper and mushrooms; drain off grease. Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix meat mixture, corn, tomatoes, chili powder and tomato juice; add drained noodles.
Mix all together. Pour into buttered pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon, removing all skins and bones. Mix all ingredients and form ball. Chill overnight and roll in 1/2 cup crushed pecans and 3 tablespoons fresh parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add cream of chicken soup, mushroom soup, enchilada sauce and taco sauce to meat.
Cook slow for 5 minutes.
Spray Pam in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer with corn tortillas.
Add layer of meat sauce.
Add layer of tortillas.
Add another layer of meat sauce.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
(Can be put in smaller dishes and frozen.
Don't cook until ready to serve.)

title: cherry o cheese pie
directions: In medium size bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add milk and stir well.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust; put pie filling on top and chill until ready to serve.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine everything but cornstarch, relish and pimentos.
Heat for 5 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Take off stove and add relish and pimentos.
Put in 4 half-pint jars and store in refrigerator.
Great to serve with hamburgers, hot dogs or vegetables.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Remove from pan. Cool on rack before slicing.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Beat until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 15 minutes longer. Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, pineapple, lime juice, chopped pecans a few drops of green food coloring.
Pour into pie crust; set for 3 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: collectors cocoa cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for 9-inch pans.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool and frost.
May be baked in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 35 to 45 minutes or until pick comes out clean.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread in egg and milk mixture.
Mix ground beef and onion together and add to the bread, eggs and milk.
Add sugar, spice, salt and pepper.
Roll into small balls.
Brown in butter.
Bake in covered dish at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Turn frequently.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Soak beans overnight in 3 cups of water.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except crumbled chips.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with crumbled chips and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: zucchini pecan bread
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix all together and bake as needed at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. This recipe keeps in the refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: county line cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, salt, lemon juice, sugar and crushed pineapple.
Cool, then add cheese and whipping cream.
Stir well. Refrigerate until set.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: In a bowl combine sugar and flour.
Add corn syrup, coconut, pineapple, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell. Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350 degree for 50 min. or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cover loosely with foil if it browns too quickly.
Cool.
Chill before cutting. Store in Refrigerator.
Yields 6-8 servings.

title: microwave pudding squares
directions: Combine milk and pudding mix in 4-cup glass measure.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring occasionally during last half of cooking time.
Set aside.
Place margarine in glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 10 seconds. Stir in graham cracker crumbs, sugar and peanut butter.
Stir until crumbly.
Press 3/4 of mixture into 1 1/2-quart baking dish; spread evenly.
Top with pudding mixture.
Freeze until solid.
Cut into squares.

title: cheese and artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock pot.
Cover and cook on low for 2 to 3 hours, until melted.
Stir well and serve with tortilla chips.

title: carrot cake
directions: Low fat option: replace 4 eggs with 1 egg yolk and 4 egg whites.
Use applesauce in place of oil.
This will make a moist cake.

title: clam chowder
directions: Measure clam juice; add water to make 2 1/2 cups.
Set clams aside.
In frypan, cook bacon until crisp; remove bacon and set aside.
Saute onions until limp; stir in potatoes and clam juice. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and simmer with celery for 10 more minutes.
Add clams and thyme.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes until clams and potatoes are tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve with a few crisp pieces of bacon in each bowl.

title: german slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion and green pepper.
In large bowl, add sugar over top.
Do not stir.
Put in saucepan the oil, vinegar, salt, celery seed and dry mustard.
Pour over shredded cabbage, onion and peppers.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate overnight.
Then stir together and serve.

title: trimming tuna toss
directions: Combine vinegar, basil, salt and pepper. Chill. In large salad bowl, break up tuna. Add lettuce, cherry tomatoes, cucumbers, onions and celery. Add vinegar mixture and toss lightly. Yields 7 servings.

title: cheesy hominy casserole
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine 1 cup of cheese, sour cream and the chilies.
Stir in the hominy.
Transfer hominy mixture to a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 main-dish servings.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box; use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a small bowl, mix peanut butter and peanut oil until smooth.
Spread on cake.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt the margarine in a large heavy pot.
Saute the vegetables in margarine for 30 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste and then the crawfish tails.
Saute for about 4 minutes and then stir in soup and water.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: crackerjacks cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Stir in oatmeal and coconut. Stir in Rice Krispies by hand.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: catfish cajun style
directions: Brush marinade on both fillets and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
However, best results are achieved with overnight marinade.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients; form into miniature balls.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes, turning once.
Serve after slightly cooled.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into bite size pieces and brown in melted fat. Combine water, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and 1 cup pineapple juice in a small pot.
Cook sauce until clear and slightly thickened.
Pour over pork.
Cover and cook 30 minutes. Add pineapple chunks and cook 2 more minutes.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: snickers cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt caramels, margarine and milk together. Pour over baked cake while hot.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon rest of cake batter over this and continue baking at 250° for 20 minutes.
Then turn oven back up to 350° and bake another 10 minutes.

title: excellent beer batter for fish
directions: Rinse fish and pat dry.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, soda and dill.
Coat fish with the flour mixture.
With the remaining flour mixture, add the lemon juice and beer.
Heat 1-inch of oil to 376°.
Dip fish in batter and fry to golden brown.
Drain and serve immediately.

title: mock chicken almond
directions: Fry and stir celery and onion for 10 minutes.
Mix altogether (except chips).
Add a handful of chips (crushed) over top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Can freeze before heating.

title: foolproof chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and Eagle Brand.
Stir in other ingredients.
Cut wax paper to 8-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan. Cool 3 hours.
Take out of pan and cut.

title: strawberry stack cake
directions: Roll biscuits very thin.
Stick several times with a fork. Fry in oil until brown and crisp, turning once.
Cool.
Place one biscuit on shallow platter; cover with berries.
Repeat until all biscuits are used, making berries the last addition.
Serve with liberal amount of whipped cream.

title: pork chops en casserole
directions: Quickly sear pork chops in skillet.
Lightly brown onions. Place chops and onions in casserole and add tomatoes, carrots, celery stalks and parsley.
Place a layer of sliced potatoes on top.
Add a little water, pepper and salt to skillet and pour into casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
When three parts cooked, pour a can of cream of mushroom soup over chops.
Mix and finish baking.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix thoroughly and pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hearty rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased 4 qt. baking dish.
Mix well and cover tightly. Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 60-70 minutes until rice is tender. Serves 12-14.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nutmeg coffee cake
directions: Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick coating; set aside.
In a small bowl combine dried fruit and milk.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a medium mixing bowl stir together oat bran baking mix, orange peel and nutmeg.

title: italian chicken nibblers
directions: Rinse chicken thoroughly, removing skin and fat.
Drain.
Fill rectangle pan with Italian dressing.
Put in chicken and marinate 1/2 hour.
Turn frequently and poke with fork.
Line broiling pan with tinfoil and spray with cooking spray.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs and place on broiling pan.
Cook, uncovered, 1 hour at 375°.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Boil potatoes and leeks in stock and salt and pepper until tender.
Puree in blender and chill.
Cut carrot in thin strips and blanch until tender.
When puree is chilled, add cold milk and cream; adjust seasonings.
Garnish with carrot strips.

title: pan fried catfish with pecan butter
directions: In
a
food processor, place 3/4 cup of pecans.
Add 1/4 cup flour,
grind
until
it becomes powdery (not too long, or else the nuts will cook
from
the heat of the machine).
Place an 8 ounce catfish fillet
in flour, take off excess flour, dip in egg mixture, then in pecan flour.
In skillet (medium heat), place 3 ounces of cooking
oil;
heat.
Place
catfish
in pan, turn
over when browned;
cook
until
tender,
about
to
5 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
After creaming Crisco and sugar, add egg and molasses.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Pour over corn flakes. Stir until well coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: chicken pot pie(350~ oven)
directions: Mix cream soups with 1 to 2 cans chicken broth at a time to desired taste.
You may not use all of broth.
Add mixed vegetables.
Line large casserole dish with 2 pie crusts and bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Add mix and cover with remaining crust.
Bake until crust is done and pie is bubbly.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Add cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar, pepper and reserved liquid and cook until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat through and serve over rice and Chinese noodles.

title: quicker comforting chicken
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, cook chicken, onion and carrots in butter until chicken is lightly browned. Add potatoes. Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes or until the carrots are tender. Add the cream, parsley, salt and pepper. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until slightly thickened. Makes 4 servings.

title: campfire roasted biscuits
directions: Leave your biscuits out of the refrigerator long enough to get the chill out of them.

Stretch each biscuit out into a strip. Cover the end of a dowel stick with one end of biscuit strip and wrap strip around stick, being careful to not leave any spaces of stick showing between the wrapped strips of dough.
Roast over hot glowing coals of campfire until biscuit puffs and is done.
Remove biscuit from stick; squeeze margarine and honey into biscuit cone and enjoy!

title: pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Cream together 2 cups powdered sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Spread mixture into baked pie crusts, then chill.
Whip cream in chilled glass bowl until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Spread this mixture on top of base mixture.
Chill thoroughly.

title: onion corn-on-the-cob
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on corn.
Wrap corn tightly in foil.
Cook over hot coals or at 425° for approximately 30 minutes.
Nice summertime recipe.

title: mushroom cream of broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli spears according to directions on package; drain off water.
Turn down on low heat.
Add can of mushroom soup and milk.
Let simmer for 5 minutes, or until creamy.

title: country captain chicken(8 servings)
directions: Cut chicken half along breast bone and back.
Cut each half into two pieces between breast and leg, making 8 pieces of chicken or else 2 chickens quartered.
Wash chicken pieces and pat dry with paper towels.
Put flour, salt and pepper in a large plastic bag. Shake seasonings together.
Season the chicken with the flour mixture until all chicken is coated.
Put butter and oil in a 6-quart Dutch oven and heat over moderately high heat.
When oil is hot, add chicken, a few pieces at a time, and cook for several minutes, browning all sides well.
Remove browned chicken; set aside until all the chicken has been cooked.
Add onions, green and red pepper, garlic and curry powder to drippings remaining in Dutch oven.
Saut vegetables, stirring constantly, until onion is soft (about 5 minutes).
Stir in tomatoes, crushing with a fork.
Add the raisins.
Bring to a boil.
Return chicken to sauce.
Simmer covered for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend together cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and peanut butter.
Pour in graham crust and freeze until ready to eat.
May freeze up to 2 months.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown ground beef.
Add onion and celery. Cook for a few minutes.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, brown sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Layer spaghetti and meat mixture in casserole dish.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 generously.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Moisten with water.
Mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper in bag.
Shake potato slices in bag.
Melt 1/3 cup butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange potatoes in single layer.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once.

title: spice cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients twice and add in 3 parts to first mixture.
Beat in milk.
Stir in egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: heath bars
directions: Boil butter and brown sugar together stirring constantly for 7 minutes. Sprinkle nuts on well greased cookie sheet. Pour mixture over nuts. Melt and spread chips over top. When hardened crack into pieces.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix boiling water and jello, then add strawberries.
Pour 1/2 jello mixture into 9 x 13 pan.
Chill.
When jell-o is set add bananas and crushed pineapple.
Top with 1/2 sour cream.
Add remaining jell-o mixture.
Chill and when set add remaining sour cream.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Brown beef very well. Dice and chop all veggies finely.
Put everything in a 4 to 6-quart pot.
Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: chalupa
directions: Cook meat and beans in separate pots. Cook meat until falls into pieces. Cook beans until very soft. Have a small amount of liquid in each. Mix meat and beans together in a large pan. To the mixture, add chili powder, chopped onion, salt, oregano, cumin and green chilies. Heat slow over low heat. Place on plate with crushed corn chips. Add meat mixture and top with chopped onion, chopped lettuce, grated cheese and taco sauce according to taste. Sour cream is optional.

title: popsicles
directions: Shake in
50 ounce container and add 2 cups cold water. Pour into
popsicle
molds
and
freeze.
This
makes 20 nice textured popsicles that won't drip while being eaten.

title: cabbage slaw dressing
directions: Mix first two ingredients and let stand 30 minutes.
Meanwhile shred cabbage very fine.
Add remaining ingredients to cream mixture and chill until ready to serve. Then add desired amount to cabbage.

title: oven fried eggplant
directions: Soak eggplant in cold water for 20 minutes.
Drain and blot dry.
Spread both sides with dressing.
Press in cheese; then in bread crumbs, coating both sides.
Arrange on a shallow pan, coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 475° for 4 minutes; turn and bake until golden brown and crisp.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, mandarin oranges and water chestnuts.
Drain well.
Allow to sit in a strainer at least 30 minutes.
Dice chicken; mix with the preceding.
Add mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Just before serving, combine with chicken mixture.
Also, mix in 1 can Chinese noodles.
Mix well.
(Very nice to serve on hot summer days.)

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until eggs stand in peaks.
Add half of sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, and beat.
Add flavoring.
Sift rest of flour and sugar together and fold in carefully.
Bake 75 minutes at 300°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large mixing bowl, mix sugar, salt, milk and butter.
Add yeast and water mixture.
Knead in flour; cover.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Knead lightly. Roll dough out to desired thickness.
Cut into rolls.
Place on greased baking pan.
Let rise.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° until golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen rolls.

title: munnie's pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix lemon juice, crushed pineapple and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Stir until sugar has dissolved.
Combine condensed milk, half and half, evaporated milk and about 1 quart whole milk in freezer can.
Slowly add the fruit mixture and stir until mixed. Freeze.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: chicken breast bordelaise
directions: Coat split chicken breasts with a light dusting of flour. Melt the 2 tablespoons of butter in a large skillet.
Very lightly saute the chicken on both sides, cooking in 2 batches if necessary.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove pieces to baking dish.
In the same skillet, in the butter remaining from the chicken, saute the sliced mushrooms briefly to coat and add the red wine.
Reduce the wine over medium heat until liquid is almost gone.
Add the 1 tablespoon butter to the same skillet, then mix in the flour.
Slowly stir in the soup and cook until the mixture boils.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Tightly cover baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with white rice.

title: apple butter cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add apple butter, water, oil, butter or squeeze Parkay and Scramblers or eggs.
Mix well. Pour into Bundt pan sprayed with Mazola.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza hamburger mix
directions: Brown the ground beef and onions.
Add spices, sauce and mushrooms.
Mix.
Spread on 15 halves of hamburger buns.
Top with cheeses.
Broil just long enough to melt cheese.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mike's american style tostada
directions: Heat beans in saucepan.
Then take chips and place some on plates.
Top with beans, lettuce, tomatoes, onions and cheese. Top all of this with ketchup.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well and use 6 level tablespoons to each cup of hot water.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn, preferably air popped. Place into paper grocery bag.
In pot on stove, bring brown sugar, syrup and butter to boil and boil 1 minute.
Add (after boiling) soda and stir until it foams. Pour over the center of the popcorn in the bag.
Shake well. Cook in microwave 1 minute.
Shake well.
Cook 1 minute.
Shake well.
Cook 1 minutes.
Shake well.
Pour into large bowl and stir occasionally as it cools to break it apart.

title: pina colada salad
directions: Fold together whipped cream, cottage cheese, pineapple and coconut.
Add gelatin powder and stir to thicken slightly.
Chill. Add rum flavoring just before serving.
Makes 10 servings.

title: "depressed" cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
In another bowl, blend butter, egg and sugar.
Mix butter mixture with dry ingredients and form dough.
Divide into 4 parts and shape each part into a roll 13 inches long, 3/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Place on ungreased sheet 4 inches apart, 2 inches from edges.
Make a depression 1/4 to 1/3-inch deep down center of log with knife handle.
Fill depression with jam and top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut diagonally.

title: deb's picante sauce
directions: Bring everything to a boil, except the peppers.
Add peppers and simmer 1 hour.
Seal in jars.
Makes 11 quarts.

title: corned beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4.

title: tuna mold
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add tuna and beat well until blended.
Pack into 4-cup mold or bowl; chill.
To serve, unmold onto a plate.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add milk and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into vanilla wafer crust and top with meringue.
Brown in oven.

title: delicious special tangy beef
directions: Combine nutmeg, cinnamon, ginger, salt and pepper.
Rub spices on meat.
Heat olive oil.
Brown meat on all sides well.
Add onions and garlic; brown them.

title: pumpkin dessert bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
With spoon, make a deep well in center.
In this well, add all the other ingredients and stir carefully, just enough to dampen all dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 loaf pans; bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Combine
cornbread and 1/2 stick melted butter.
Spread a layer of this in the bottom of a greased casserole or baking dish. Mix
together
the
remaining
ingredients
(melt
the remaining butter);
pour
on the cornbread layer and top with the remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Place bread in bottom.
Sprinkle browned sausage over bread.
Add beaten eggs to half and half and salt to taste.
Pour over sausage and bread. Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all
ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Lay bacon over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar,
flour and cocoa.
Add milk, butter and salt. Cook until it boils.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Stir.
Dough should be fairly stiff. Divide into 5 or 6 balls and refrigerate several hours.
Roll out small portions of dough on a floured board.
Cut in various shapes.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage-spinach loaf
directions: Thaw bread dough and let rise according to directions.
Cook and drain sausage; season with 1 teaspoon Italian seasonings. Thaw spinach and drain well.

title: special brownies
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill for several hours.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken breast until well done.
Cook spaghetti noodles until done.
Tear chicken into small pieces.
Mix margarine, green pepper, onion, about 1/4 cup of milk, cheese and almonds in with the spaghetti and chicken.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and remaining almonds.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: apple raisin loaf
directions: I use 2 cups self-rising flour instead of 2 cups of flour and the baking powder and baking soda.
Cream the butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy, then add lemon juice, milk, applesauce and raisins.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan at 350° until done, about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: won tons
directions: Stir-fry together selected meat, eggs, shredded cabbage and chopped onions (diced). Wet the egg roll wraps 1 at a time in water. Fill them with ingredients and roll tightly. Drop into already preheated hot grease. Do not pile on top of each other; will stick together. Lay out on paper towels on long cookie sheet to harden and to absorb the grease. Douse with couple squirts of soy sauce for flavor. Makes about 30 won tons total.

title: snickers delight
directions: Cut up apple into slices.
Break up Snickers bars.
Combine apples and Snickers into bowl with the Cool Whip.
Mix until coated.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and peppers; drain.
Combine beef mixture, tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic.
Simmer on medium heat until warm.
In a small mixing bowl, mix sour cream and egg.
Add to beef mixture and simmer for 10 minutes.
Tear biscuits apart in the middle, keeping them round.
Place biscuits on bottom of greased baking dish, just cover the bottom and save half for the top.
Pour beef mixture over biscuits; sprinkle half of the cheese over beef mixture.
Place remaining biscuits on top and sprinkle the top of the biscuits with the remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except pizza sauce; stir just until moistened.
Spread dough on bottom of greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into 3 x 1-inch rectangles.
Serve hot with pizza sauce.
Makes 50 pizza sticks.

title: lance's peanut butter and raisin sandwich
directions: Open bread.
Spread peanut butter on both sides.
Sprinkle raisins on one side.
Close sandwich.
Use cookie cutters to make special shaped sandwiches.

title: oatmeal scones
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients, then add oatmeal.
Melt butter and let cool.
Add additional ingredients and stir.
Fold in dry mixture.
Form into ball and put on floured surface.
Form in 8 inch circle and cut into 8 wedges.
Place wedges 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no-fat carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat 1 cup honey and applesauce until thick.
Add vanilla, carrot and pineapple.
Combine remaining ingredients in mixing bowl; stir into wet mixture until completely moistened and evenly blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Serve plain or with cream cheese frosting.

title: banana poppy seed muffins
directions: Mash bananas in a small bowl.
Mix egg, sugar and oil in a large bowl.
Add and mix in the milk, poppy seed and bananas.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Mix dry ingredients with liquid ingredients.
Line 12 cupcake tins with paper liners; fill half full with batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry flummery
directions: In medium saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch and salt until no lumps remaining.
Stir in milk and half and half until smooth.
Stir constantly over medium heat.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
In small bowl, beat yolks until smooth.
Gradually stir 1/3 of hot mixture into egg yolks, then stir back into hot mixture in saucepan.
Over low heat, cook and stir for 3 to 4 minutes, until thick and glossy; do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.

title: mexican manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 12 x 8-inch baking dish with light vegetable spray.
Cook shells as label directs.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine cooked chicken, Ricotta, scallion, olives, pimiento, parsley or cilantro, garlic and hot pepper sauce.
Use a teaspoon to stuff cooked shells with mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Top with cheese and tomato salsa.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: "big mama's squash casserole"
directions: Cook squash, unpeeled in small amount of water.
Drain and mash.
Beat eggs and milk slightly.
Add to squash.
Add cracker crumbs, onion, cheese and salt.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat tomato soup.
Dissolve gelatin in soup.
Mix well with other ingredients and chill.

title: mom's casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef. While the beef is browning, combine in a mixing bowl the cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream and chopped scallions.
When the beef is browned, drain the grease, then stir in the canned tomatoes and tomato sauce.
In a greased 3-quart casserole dish, layer in this order:
half of the noodles, all of the cheese mixture, remaining noodles and all of the tomato and beef mixture. Cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: cheddar taters
