directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: fresh fruit bowl
directions: In large bowl, stir gelatin into boiling water until dissolved.
Stir in lemonade concentrate and ginger ale.
Add mixed fruit and toss gently until well coated.
Cover. Refrigerate at least 4 hours until chilled.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons or 24 (1 cup) servings.

title: joy's stained glass candy
directions: Bring almost to 300°.
Add a color.
Boil to 300°.
Then add 1 teaspoon flavor (1/8 ounce bottle).
Remove from heat.
Stir a couple of minutes.
Pour into well-greased large flat pan.
It should be 1/8-inch thick when poured.
When cold, break and place in powdered sugar.
Repeat for each color.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Have paper removed from candy. Divide cookie roll into 24 balls. Place each ball into ungreased small muffin tins and bake cookies 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven. Remove from oven and push a peanut butter cup in center of cookie. Let cool in tin.

title: yummy snack
directions: Cover bottom of cookie sheet with soda crackers.
Sprinkle with sugar and pour margarine over sugar.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and while hot, cover with chips.
When melted, spread chips evenly over cracker mixture and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill and break into serving pieces.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and salt.
Cook until soft balls forms when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Cool 5 minutes.
Beat until mixture is creamy and begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut in squares.

title: cherry delight
directions: After baking, cut cake into bite size pieces.
Place 1/2 of cake in bottom of rectangular glass dish.
Spread pie filling over cake.
Put other 1/2 of cake pieces on top of filling.
Mix pudding and milk and fold in sour cream.
Pour over cake pieces.
Spread over the top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and let set for several hours before serving.

title: toasty egg
directions: Take 1 slice of any bread you like.
Take piece about size of half dollar from center of bread.
Butter both sides and place in skillet.
Cook and turn to slightly brown both sides.
Break egg into hole in center of bread.
Fry, turning over until approximately "over easy."
Salt and pepper both sides to taste.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease large baking dish; put in rice, cream of chicken soup, water, lemon juice and onion soup mix.
Lay chicken pieces over mixture, then salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water for 10 minutes.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in dissolved yeast and eggs.
Gradually add flour, stirring with wooden spoon after each addition.
Knead continuously to a smooth elastic dough. Cover and let rise until double in bulk, about one hour.
Punch dough down; divide in two.
Roll each half on lightly floured board to a 12-inch circle of 1/4pinch thickness.
Brush with melted butter.
Cut each circle into 16 wedge-shaped pieces; roll each wedge, starting with rounded edge and rolling to point.
Arrange far apart on greased baking sheet with points underneath.
Brush with melted butter, cover and let rise until light, 45 to 50 minutes.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 32 rolls.

title: quick shake pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put eggs and milk into Quick Shake and shake vigorously (hold spout seal).
Add dry ingredients and shake again.
Pour mixture into greased and floured pan.
Bake until firm (2 to 4 minutes).
Add toppings as desired.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes until done.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs, basil, oregano, salt and pepper in a bowl.
In another bowl, put the beaten egg.
Dip each chicken breast in the egg.
Then dip in the bread crumb mixture, turning to coat lightly.

title: popcorn scramble
directions: Bring margarine, sugar and Karo to a boil.
Let boil for 5 minutes, without stirring.
Take off heat; stir in soda and pour on cereal, nuts and popcorn.
Stir until mixed well.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: pea and cheese salad
directions: Chill peas.
Combine celery, cheese, pickles, onions and chilled peas.
Add mayonnaise to moisten and salt and pepper. Serve on salad greens.

title: mom's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) pans or oblong pan at 350° until cake tests done.
This cake is for anyone who still likes to dunk their cake.

title: easy chicken wings
directions: Preheat oil in deep fryer at 400°.
If chicken wings are frozen, make sure they are thawed completely.
Submerge wings into deep fryer slowly; cook thoroughly until done.
Remove from deep fryer and blot excess oil with a paper towel.
Combine butter, hot sauce and Zesty Italian Dressing in container with lid. Add hot chicken wings to mixture, shake vigorously and remove.
Place on platter and enjoy!

title: old-fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until chicken is tender.
Remove bones and skin.
Set aside 2 cups of broth.
Put chicken back into broth and boil.
With one cup of water, make a stiff dough.
Roll thin and cut into strips, about 2-inches long.
Drop into chicken, a small part at a time.
Cook without lid about 5 minutes.
Cover and cook about 5 more minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix salt, cornstarch, sugar and vinegar.
Bring sauce to a boil, stirring constantly.
Lower heat and let simmer several minutes.
Add butter to the sauce.
Drain beets,
add to the sauce and cook slowly until the beets are hot.
Serve at once.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Parboil vegetables.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and cheese.
Mix with vegetables.
Melt remaining margarine; mix with crackers, then pour over top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Boil sweet potatoes with peel on until tender.
Remove from heat.
Cool and peel.
Cut in halves and place in baking dish. Pour pineapple over sweet potatoes.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top; dot with oleo.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Place marshmallows all over.
Put under broiler until brown.
Serve hot.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cherries and 1/2 cup sugar.
Melt butter in casserole. Mix batter of flour, 1 cup sugar, milk, baking powder and salt. Pour batter on melted butter.
Add cherries.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or longer until brown and batter comes to top.

title: sausage potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and green pepper in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add sausage and toss lightly.
Combine cream cheese, milk and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and flour.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: mango salad
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together at once.
Pour into mold or bowl and let set.

title: super blueberry cheesecake(diet)
directions: Combine whipping cream, gelatin and sweetener in saucepan; stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Stir in bowl lemon rind, lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Add to cheese. Add cream-gelatin mixture.
Beat very smooth.
Pour into an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Chill about 1/2 hour until mixture is causing a ripple effect.
Chill until firm.
Remove.
Serves 6.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let butter set at room temperature to become soft.
Grate cheese fine, then also set out at room temperature to become softer.
To cheese add salt, red pepper, then butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour; mix with fork.
This will look like meal at first.
Shape into dough.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick on waxed paper. Cut in 1/2-inch strips.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 15 minutes in 325° oven.

title: microwave cherry dessert
directions: Place cherry pie filling in ungreased 9-inch pie dish (glass). Beat butter on high until smooth, about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in brown sugar, oats, flour and cinnamon.
Mixture will be crumbly. Sprinkle over pie filling.
Press down lightly. Microwave on High power for 8 minutes or until hot and bubbly in the center. Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or plain.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl; mix well with fork.
Add shortening and mix with fork until crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat together with fork, 1/2 cup water, vinegar and the egg.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough into 5 portions; shape into flat round patties ready for rolling.
Wrap each portion in plastic or waxed paper and chill at least 1/2 hour.
Can be frozen at this point or keeps in refrigerator for up to 3 days.
I think this recipe tastes better after freezing.
This is a recipe I use all the time.
It is handy to keep some in the freezer.
No matter how much this dough is handled, it will still be flaky and tender.
This makes it great for "young chefs" who like to roll and re-roll the pie dough.
Kids can cut shapes and sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl. Beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract in large bowl. Add eggs. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels and nuts. Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 5 dozen.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Marinate chicken overnight in Italian dressing in refrigerator.
Just before cooking, sprinkle Cavender's seasoning on both sides.
Grill until done on outdoor or indoor grill.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Boil peeled and cut up potatoes about 20 minutes.
Drain.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer potatoes, cheese and dot with margarine. Pour milk over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° until brown on top.

title: coconut cake
directions: You will need thread.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll biscuits flat; fill with seasoned apples (whatever spices you use in fried pies).
Place in large baking dish in a single layer.
Bring to a boil the sugar, margarine, vanilla and 7-Up. Pour over dumplings.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla in bowl; mix well with wooden spoon.
Shape by tablespoons into balls; place about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness by pressing in crisscross design with fork.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yields 1 to 1 1/2 dozen.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix together sour cream, creamed corn, eggs and oil.
Add corn meal and sugar; blend.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan until brown, about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: netherlands beef birds
directions: Cut steak in 6 pieces; with meat hammer or edge of heavy saucer, pound until quite thin.
Sprinkle one side with salt, pepper and marjoram.
Place an onion on each piece; roll up.
Tie with string, or secure with skewers or toothpicks.
Coat meat rolls with flour.
In heavy skillet, brown rolls evenly in oil.
Pour off fat.
Stir in tomato paste, water, horseradish and parsley. Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla butter frosting
directions: Blend milk with flour until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Cool thoroughly.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add milk mixture, vanilla and food coloring.
Beat until smooth.
Makes enough for 3 large layers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chinese spaghetti dinner
directions: Prepare spaghetti as label directs.
Drain and return spaghetti to pot; keep warm.
In a 12-inch skillet, in hot salad oil, cook mushrooms, green onions and carrots until tender-crisp, stirring quickly and frequently.
Spoon mixture onto spaghetti. Add soy sauce, sugar and pepper.
Toss to mix all ingredients. Serve.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: In a small skillet, saute the onion in the oil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in the garlic; remove from the heat and spoon into large bowl and cool completely.
To the onion-garlic mixture, add the marjoram, beef, eggs, bread crumbs, club soda, green pepper, Cheddar cheese, 1 cup barbecue sauce and ground pepper to taste; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Form the mixture into a loaf in a lightly oiled 10-inch ovenproof baking dish.
Spread the remaining 3 tablespoons barbecue sauce over the top and side of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly. Cool.
In bottom of pie shell, place fresh strawberries.
Pour cooled mixture over berries.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: old south chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add nutmeg, beaten eggs, whiskey and milk, mixing well after each addition. Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease pie plate. Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Stir in salt. Spread in pie plate. Sprinkle cheese. Stir remaining ingredients with a fork until blended. Pour into pie plate. Bake 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sirloin steak marinade
directions: Marinate beef for 6 to 8 hours and broil or grill to desired taste.
Also excellent with chicken or turkey breast fillets, broiled or grilled.

title: lemon pepper toast
directions: Mix softened oleo and lemon pepper.
Spread on each slice of bread and restack as a loaf.
Cut in four finger-size slices. Bake 45 minutes at 275°.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes; add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon mixture.
Stir together dry ingredients; add to batter.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper and cover with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Turn on linen dish towel covered with confectioners sugar.
Remove wax paper.
Roll tight and cool.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Note:
Need 1 box tiny cupcake papers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: If round steak is used, cut into small pieces. Brown meat and onion in skillet. Add mushroom soup, salt, pepper and garlic salt. Simmer until meat is tender. Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add sour cream and noodles.
Serve.

title: reuben spread
directions: Put in 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° until bubbly, at least 30 minutes. Serve with party rye bread slices.

title: maids of honor
directions: Mix all ingredients, except jam.
Fill each cup in a miniature muffin pan halfway with mix.
Make indentation with spoon and fill with jam of choice (raspberry, etc.).
Bake at 375° until crisp. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Heat water and margarine until it boils and margarine is completely melted.
Remove from heat and immediately add flour and salt; mix well.
It will be stiff.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with spoon after each one.
Put into cookie press with cream puff tip and press out to desired length onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
When cool, poke a hole in one end with knife or spoon handle and fill with filling, then frost.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all together.
Beat until smooth.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Mold into ball and roll in ground peanuts.
Serve with crackers for a snack.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown turkey in heavy frypan and drain off all fat.
Add onions and cook until transparent.
Add all spices, Mexicorn, stewed tomatoes, puree and half enchilada sauce.
Cook on low heat until mixture has thickened.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers, cutting out the center only.
Boil peppers for about 15 minutes.
Cook potatoes and onion together until potatoes are almost done.
Mix all ingredients together and stuff into boiled peppers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until stuffing is done.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Combine all
ingredients
in
order
given.
Mix
well. Pour into a greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool completely.

title: nutty clusters
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in double boiler over hot water. Remove from heat.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, put rice and water.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Spoon celery soup and chicken rice soup onto chicken.
Sprinkle with soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake 90 minutes at 350°.

title: the potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bag, add all ingredients. Shake until evenly coated.
Place potatoes in shallow baking or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Garnish if desired with parsley flakes. Makes 8 servings.

title: enchiladas
directions: Beat eggs with milk and sift in the flour and salt.
Stir in cornmeal and beat until smooth.
Fry in pan and tip pan so it spreads to the edges of 6 to 8-inch pan.
Fry on low heat until tip is dull, turn end and fry on other side.
Do not brown.
(I dump it all together and beat it with electric beater.)

title: oriental flank steak
directions: In large non-aluminum shallow baking dish or plastic bag, combine all ingredients except steak.

title: chillo
directions: Chop onion and saute in crock-pot.
Put the Velveeta cheese and half can to whole can of evaporated milk.
Put hot sauce in crock-pot.
Heat.
Stir occasionally.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Melt 1 cube of butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix 2 cups of water with 2 cups of sugar in a saucepan and heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Mix 1/2 cup of shortening, flour and milk until dough leaves the side of the bowl.
Knead until smooth and roll into large rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Mix apples with cinnamon and spread evenly over dough.
Roll jelly roll style and seal edges with a little water.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices and place in pan with melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup around and over top of rolls.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Real good.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: In saucepan, blend blackberry juice, 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
When thickened, add blackberries and set aside.
Blend sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Add melted butter. Pour batter into buttered baking dish.
Add blackberries on top. Batter will form crust on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix and let sit overnight.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix as listed.
Cook, stirring continually, until thick.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Pour into a cooked pie shell.
Top with egg white meringue and brown.
This is a very old recipe.

title: fannie mae fudge
directions: Put milk, butter and sugar in 4-quart heavy saucepan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved and butter melted.
Add
marshmallows.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and add all the chocolate.
Stir until chocolate is melted and the mixture is uniform in color.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered cake pan.
Allow to cool before cutting.
Make no substitutions.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together.
Add chow mein noodles.
Add one peanut at a time.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Cut baked potatoes into quarters lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Brush shells with melted butter.
Bake shells at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Bake just until cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and garnish with more bacon bits.

title: altar potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on and grate like cabbage when cooked.
Heat in pan the potatoes and remaining ingredients.
Add 8 ounces of sour cream.
Sprinkle buttered bread or corn flake crumbs on top and place in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook beef and onion, drain.
Stir in soup, enchilada sauce, milk and chilies.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a small skillet, dip tortillas in hot oil, just until limp (about 5 seconds) on each side and drain.
Reserve 1/2 cup cheese.
Place 1/4 cup of the cheese on each tortilla and sprinkle with olives.
Roll up tortillas and place in sauce in skillet.
Cover and cook until heated through, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with reserved 1/2 cup cheese.
Cover and cook just until cheese melts.

title: savory vegetable cheesecake(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Set grated zucchini in a colander over sink or bowl.
Salt lightly and let stand 15 minutes.
Squeeze out moisture.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in dish.
Add drained corn.
In separate bowl, mix soup, sour cream, cheese and onion together.
Put on top of corn.

title: sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, honey and brown sugar in bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.
Mix well and spread evenly in pan. Sprinkle raisins evenly over margarine mixture.
Arrange biscuits in pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven and let sit 1 minute.
Invert onto serving plate and serve warm.

title: shiny top cobbler
directions: Spread fruit in well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix together to form thick batter: flour, 1/2 the sugar, milk, butter (cut in small pieces), baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Spoon over fruit and spread to edge of pan.
Set aside.
Mix remaining sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
(Put on cookie sheet; it boils over!)

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook slowly and stir constantly.
Cook until thick.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas. Pour filling over and repeat.

title: sausage scallopini
directions: Place sausage in frying pan and pour in about 1 cup of water. Bring to boil and let simmer until sausage looks white.
Pour off water, then brown evenly on both sides.
Add sliced pepper, onion and mushrooms and saute until golden brown.
Add tomato sauce and simmer about 1/2 hour.
Correct seasoning.
Good with warm Italian bread.

title: apple stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Saute celery and apples in 2 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes. Stir in crumbs and spices.
Place mix on chicken and roll up. Heat 2 tablespoons butter.
Brown chicken all over.
Add sherry and broth.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven while combining the ingredients.
Drain salmon, save liquid.
Remove any large bones.
Squeeze juice of lemon. Chop onion in small pieces.
Combine salmon and bread crumbs. Crumble cheese crackers.
Add all remaining ingredients in medium bowl.
Mix well with fork until blended thoroughly.
(Economical, easy and quick for lunch or dinner!)

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Brown flour, onion, pepper and garlic in shortening. Cook until tender. Add shrimp, tomatoes, water, rice and salt. Cook 25 minutes or until tender.

title: martha's syrup tea cake
directions: Work flour in and roll out.
Cut and bake in 350°
oven. Makes a lot.

title: chicken salad
directions: Pull skin from chicken breasts.
Then cut meat from bones. Dice meat.
Combine with carrots, celery, onion, water, chicken broth or chicken bouillon cube and salt in a large frying pan. Heat to boiling.
Cover.

title: fresh grapefruit cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with grapefruit juice, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Gradually add milk.
Stir in grapefruit rind and vanilla; mix well.

title: christmas holly wreath
directions: Place margarine and marshmallows in a pan and keep stirring until all is melted; add vanilla.
Add food coloring (enough for a good color).
Add cornflakes slowly until all are coated.
Put on a cookie sheet with waxed paper and shape into small rounds and put finger in center to make wreath.
Add red hearts as desired. Let set and keep cool.
Put a little oil on hands when putting finger in center of wreath.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream both sugars, salt and margarine; mix well.
Mix flour, soda and baking powder together; mix good.
Add to sugar mixture. Mix in beaten egg; mix well.
Add oats, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet, approximately 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Boil skinned chicken in pieces for 2 hours to obtain broth. Add vegetables and other leftover vegetables (green beans, corn). Bring to boil and simmer 1 hour. Soup will keep 1 week and can be frozen. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lottie moon cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg, then add flour and milk. Drop on cookie sheet and cook until golden.
Bake at 475°.

title: country style pheasant
directions: Rinse pheasants with cold water and pat dry with paper towels. On a pie plate, combine flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in the flour mixture using fingertips to pat coating on the meat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook vermicelli; drain.
Add Accent, oil and lemon juice; marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl beat cheese with fork until smooth.
Gradually stir in pineapple, pecans (1 cup), green peppers, onions and salt. Chill. Shape into ball and roll in remaining pecans.

title: pastry for pies
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Add 3 1/2 more cups of flour, mixing with a spoon with each addition.
Generously flour surface of area. Take 1/4 of the dough and make into a ball.
Flour the surface and roll out to a size larger than the pie tin and 1/4-inch thick. Fold in half and half again and lift into the pie tin.
Form against the sides and crimp the edges.
Makes enough for 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender or food processor.

title: barbecued short ribs
directions: Brown meat in shortening in
a skillet.
Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and
simmer
for
1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
The ribs can also be covered and baked at 350° until tender, approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixing bowl except brown sugar and nuts.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle mixture with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Spoon hot butter glaze over warm cake.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Crumble, brown and drain sausage after cooked.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 13 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together. Salt and pepper.
Ready to serve.

title: cherry pie supreme
directions: Line a 7-inch pie pan with crust and spoon in 1/2 cherry pie filling.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Work cheese with a fork to soften.
Work sugar in cheese until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Pour cream mixture into hot pie filling in crust.
Cool completely before serving.
Spoon sour cream around ring of pie.
Spoon remaining pie filling in center.

title: pocket bread
directions: Mix together milk, salt, sugar, yeast, oil and about 6 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead dough on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in bowl that has been brushed with oil.
Turn greased side up and cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour.

title: caramel biscuit ring
directions: Grease fluted pan.
Preheat oven to 400°. In a saucepan, combine sugar, nuts, margarine and water.
Heat until margarine melts.

title: country club dressing
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, water and seasonings together in blender or food processor.
Gradually add salad oil while blending. Refrigerate.

title: banana sour cream walnut loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and bananas and beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add alternately with sour cream to banana mixture, stirring just to blend.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon batter in a 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan that has been greased and floured on bottom only.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Let stand in pan on rack 20 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Wrap in plastic wrap to keep.

title: pineapple spread
directions: Mix together and spread
on crackers or use as open-faced sandwiches.

title: egg roll
directions: Whisk eggs; mix sugar, mirin, dash of soy sauce and salt in dashi broth, then blend in whisked eggs.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except nuts and raisins.
After mixing, add nuts and raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 6 dozen.

title: creamy zucchini casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in butter until almost done.
Stir in Stove Top stuffing with seasoning, cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir together lightly.
Put into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften	cream
cheese.	Add
remaining ingredients, mix well. Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers or chips.

title: vegi curry rice
directions: Cook rice and combine all ingredients, except cheese in large casserole dish.
Dice margarine and distribute well.
After all ingredients are well mixed, taste and add additional seasoning, if needed.
Once satisfied, slice cheese and lay on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients. Mix liquids with dry ingredients; stir well.
Put in an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex chicken salad
directions: In large skillet, saute the chicken, jalapenos and onion in butter until chicken is no longer pink. Add the cream cheese, tomatoes, salsa and salt; stir until blended. Serve over lettuce; sprinkle with cheese, olives and tortilla chips. Serves 6.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in buttered casserole at 400° for 25 minutes.
Quick, but very good.

title: big toll house cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Beat butter, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs gradually; add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spread in greased 14 or 15-inch pizza pan or use greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into wedges.

title: two chess pies
directions: Mix all the ingredients with the mixer.
Pour into 2 unbaked regular pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Pour cereal and nuts in a large container.
Mix remaining ingredients in a saucepan and heat until butter is melted.
Pour over cereal.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 175°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Pour out on paper towels and store in airtight container.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Pour into crust.
Chill overnight.
Garnish with a lemon twist and serve.

title: spaghetti
directions: Combine tomato sauce and spices in saucepan.
Allow to simmer on low heat for over 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cheese and powdered sugar.
Add peanut butter. Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell and freeze until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Blend until appearance of biscuit mix.
Spread half of mixture on baked pie shell.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice or dice zucchini into a frying pan or small kettle.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and water.
Let cook for about 25 minutes. While you beat the eggs, add the other ingredients to the eggs, then the zucchini.
Bake in a 375° oven until set (about 30 minutes).

title: hawaiian stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound the chicken breasts to 1/4 inch thickness.
Mix hot water and margarine in bowl.
Stir in stuffing mix, pepper and half of pineapple and syrup.
Spoon stuffing mix evenly on chicken; roll tightly and secure with toothpicks.
Place in 9-inch square pan, putting the remaining stuffing in the center.

title: svengali tomatoes
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
Simmer for 8 to 10 minutes. Serve warm or cold.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Arrange 6 slices toast in ungreased oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix tuna, onion and mayonnaise; spread over toast in pan.
Top each slice toast with 1 slice cheese; place remaining slices toast on cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour on center of toast, spreading within 2-inches of edges.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it strings.
Add peanuts. Cook at medium heat until golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Stir well.
Add baking soda.
Stir well.
Pour immediately on a greased cookie sheet.
After it gets hard, break into pieces.

title: cherry squares
directions: Add cherry pie filling on top of crust.
Mix together remaining ingredients. Spread on top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until brown, at 350°.

title: pecan cheese wafers
directions: Mix all together with hands.
Divide in half; make 2 rolls (about size of silver dollar).
Roll.
Put in wax paper.
Secure ends of paper.
Chill until firm.
Remove wax paper and slice. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Freeze other roll (uncooked) for later use, if desired.

title: come back salad dressing
directions: Mix and shake together in jar.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a mixing bowl. After mixing well, stir in all other ingredients. Then place in a greased and floured pan.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken and celery until tender.
Place chicken and celery in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix and add soup, mayonnaise and water chestnuts.
Use 1/4 to 1/2 cup of liquid, as needed.
Spread mixture on top of chicken.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil; cook until thick and bubbly.
Add lemon juice.
Fill 7 hot quart jars about 1/3 full with filling.
Pack tightly with pared and sliced apples.
Seal. Process 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zangy sausage and cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes with green chilies in crock-pot.
Cook in skillet the ground beef and then sausage. Drain well.
Mix meats in crock-pot with cheese.
Add Blue cheese mix.
Serve warm with tortilla chips or crackers.
Makes a lot.

title: easy cool banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding with cold milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip to pudding mixture and mix well.
Make layers of vanilla wafers and bananas.
Pour mixture over each layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In 12-inch skillet, medium-high, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Cook zucchini with 1/4 teaspoon salt until tender-crisp.
Remove to bowl.
In same skillet with 1 tablespoon oil, cook eggplant, onion and 1/2 teaspoon salt until eggplant begins to brown slightly.
Add pepper and 1 tablespoon oil until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, black pepper, basil, sugar and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add zucchini and heat through.
Meanwhile, cook noodles; drain.
To serve, toss noodles with vegetable mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: hot cheesy potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, peel and slice.
Add onion, mayonnaise, dry mustard, bacon, black pepper and Velveeta.
Mix together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hardy soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together and drain off grease.
Add remainder of ingredients and cook for 1 hour on medium heat.
May add broken up noodles, if desired.

title: osgood pies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add vinegar, spices, dates and nuts.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add last and pour in crust. Bake in a slow oven.

title: herb-baked chicken fingers
directions: Dissolve bouillon and mustard in boiling water.
Add garlic and flour ingredients.
Stir well.
Place chicken strips in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, cheese and water; beat with electric beater until dissolved.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice and beat again.
Chill until syrupy.
Add celery, nuts and pineapple.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook onion and pepper in butter until done, then push aside in skillet.
Cook bacon and bologna, in pieces, on other side of skillet.
Cook until done.
Put in rice and 1/4 bottle of soy sauce.
Put in garlic.
Break egg and stir until done.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring to boil the butter and water.
Add flour and let cool. Add eggs, beating 1 at a time.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder; set aside. Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and mix well.
Then add vanilla, salt and cocoa; mix.
Alternately add flour mixture and water.
Add sauerkraut.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan or angel food cake pan at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: Using a large pot, boil chicken for 1 hour, then add potatoes, carrots, onions and curry; boil 15 minutes, then add butter, salt and pepper.
Boil 15 minutes.
Enjoy with rice or French bread.

title: tamale pie casserole
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until lightly browned, stirring to keep crumbly.
Drain excess fat.
Add ground beef.
Cook and stir until browned.
Stir in garlic, celery and onion; cook until crisp-tender.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, corn, salt to taste and chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Slowly stir in corn meal and cook until thickened.
Stir in olives. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole and top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: plum good cake
directions: Coat raisins with 1/2 cup of the flour.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple-banana cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Dice the bananas; measure the quantity and add them to the dry ingredients along with oil, vanilla, eggs and crushed pineapple.
Stir and blend, but do not beat.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fresh lemon sherbet
directions: Beat egg whites until mixture makes stiff peaks when beater is lifted. Gradually add sugar, beating continuously. Fold in thawed lemonade gently. Freeze in an ice tray.

title: walnut balls
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix by hand.
Form into small balls, walnut size, and roll into slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll into chopped nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and whipping cream.
Mix well. Pour into freezer can.
Add Eagle Brand.
Stir well.
Add milk to fill line of freezer and freeze.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Beat together the eggs, milk, sugar and lemon and put over double boiler and cook until thick and smooth.
Cool.

title: zesty salad
directions: Chop tomatoes, green peppers and onions.
Slice cucumber, carrots and radishes.
Break cauliflower up.
Pour Zesty Italian dressing over and let set 3 to 4 hours.
Keep in refrigerator. You can keep adding vegetables to dressing.

title: lamb shanks with mustard and horseradish gravy
directions: About 2 hours and 15 minutes before serving, in Dutch oven or other large, heavy pan, over medium heat, in hot shortening, brown shanks well.
In a small bowl, mix mustard, horseradish, salt, M.S., paprika, pepper and 1 cup water.
Pour over shanks.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours, or until meat is tender, adding more water if necessary.
In warm, deep platter, mix rice and peas.
Place shanks on top.

title: tuna noodle
directions: Drain noodles.
Add tuna with mushroom soup; add milk.
Stir well.
Heat until hot.

title: ladyfingers or clothespin cookies
directions: Cream oleo and cottage cheese.
Add flour and mix well.
Dough should be soft but not sticky.
Roll pieces and cut into 3 or 4-inch strips.
Roll onto foil-covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Fill with cooked icing when cool.

title: "oh boy" waffles (or pancakes)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in small mixing bowl. In larger mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk and oil. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Bake in a waffle iron.

title: apple crisp
directions: Lay apples in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Mix other ingredients.
Crumble over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 325° until set.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Mix together and pour in 3 cake pans and cook until done.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, confectioners sugar, 2 cups flour and salt and pat evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix together eggs, 6 tablespoons flour, lemon rind, sugar and lemon juice. Spread over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sift confectioners sugar on top.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake in oven 45 minutes at 325°.

title: 1846 corn dodgers
directions: Sift cornmeal, sugar and salt together.
Add milk to egg, then add milk-egg mixture to cornmeal mixture.
Pour over this enough boiling water to make fairly stiff dough.
Beat well.
Use deep bowl.
Wet hands and shape dough into small round patties.
Brown in butter on both sides and drain on paper towels.

title: salisbury steak deluxe
directions: Combine and stir first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 of soup mixture. Form into patties.
Brown; drain drippings from pan.
Combine rest of soup mixture plus water.
Pour over patties.
Cook for 20 minutes on medium-low.
Stir gravy occasionally.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix cake mix and walnuts according to box directions and add walnuts to mix.

title: taco roll
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet until well done. Pour taco seasoning mix over hamburger and mix; let cool. Once it is cooled, add cheese.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter in bowl.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine cream cheese and confectioners sugar in mixer bowl; beat until smooth.
Blend in whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Stir in strawberries.
Chill until partially set.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Chill until set.
Yield: 15 servings.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Cool in pan.
Add pineapple.
Blend whipping cream and cream cheese together to make soft, then add to jello mixture. Sprinkle nuts on top and put in refrigerator overnight.
Use a 2-inch deep pan.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in balls the size of walnuts.
Melt 1/2 stick of paraffin and 6 ounces chocolate chips in a double boiler. Roll balls in chocolate mixture using toothpicks.
Place on wax paper to harden.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Layer noodles, meat, cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Make 2 layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mint-orangeade cooler
directions: Bring 1 cup orange juice to boil.
Add to sugar and mint. Cool.
Strain.
Add 1 cup of orange juice and lime juice.
Just before serving, add sparkling water.
Pour into 4 tall ice-filled glasses.
Makes 4 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk.
Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.

title: indian tacos
directions: With your hands, mix flour, dry milk, baking powder, salt and shortening.
Add milk.
Roll out on floured board.
Fry in 1-inch hot oil until brown.
Top with favorite taco filling or fruit or etc.

title: quick and easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Thaw dough according to package.
Roll out to 6 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cover the rectangle evenly with softened butter. Blend together sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Sprinkle evenly over rectangle.
Roll up tightly, starting at 6-inch side of rectangle. Seal by pinching edges of roll together.
Cut roll into 12 slices.
Place cut side up in 8-inch greased pan.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 18 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan when cool. Frost with vanilla icing.

title: orange-carrot salad
directions: Place gelatin in a medium-sized bowl.
Stir in boiling water until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in orange juice and chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Fold in shredded carrot, raisins and nuts.
Turn mixture into a 9-inch square pan and chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brown sugar chews
directions: Mix brown sugar with butter until well mixed. Add flour, eggs, baking powder, and nuts. Then add vanilla flavoring last. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Allow butter and cream cheese to come to room temperature.
Add vanilla to softened butter.
Mix in cream cheese.
Stir in sugar. Beat until smooth and spreadable.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In second bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Spread bean dip on bottom of a large shallow dish.
Top with avocado mixture.
Layer with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, tomatoes and olives. Cover with shredded cheese.
Serve chilled with round tortilla chips.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine peanut butter, butter and sugar.
Mix thoroughly until mixture can be shaped into 1-inch balls.
(Add 1/4 cup water if needed.)
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over low heat.
Shape 1-inch balls and pierce each ball with toothpick and dip into chocolate mixture to partially cover.
Set aside on wax paper until hardened.

title: delightful turkey soup
directions: Place all ingredients except peas and broccoli in Dutch oven. Simmer 50 minutes.
Add peas and broccoli and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook chicken (covered with water, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and 1/2 onion).
Cook 1/2 onion in chicken stock until tender.
Add soup, green chilies, Ro-Tel, pepper and garlic salt.
Simmer and stir until well blended.
Add chicken and stir in sour cream. Remove from heat.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with butter. Line the bottom with one layer corn tortillas, torn or cut.
Layer with chicken mixture (1/3 mixture).
Layer with cheeses.
Continue to layer, then bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss all ingredients in bowl.
Add dressing.

title: marinated shrimp and pasta salad
directions: In small jar with
lid	combine oil, lemon juice, salad dressing mix and horseradish; mix well.
In large bowl combine all ingredients; toss
with
dressing.	Cover;	chill
several hours. Serve on lettuce if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mushroom meat loaf
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Pour mushroom soup on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas divinity
directions: Butter 9-inch square pan.
Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in saucepan.
Cook to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Then reduce heat and continue cooking to hard ball stage or 250° on candy thermometer.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease pie plate well with butter. Arrange apples in dish. Melt butter, then add other ingredients and mix well. When mixed, spread over apples-then bake slowly at 350° for 30-35 minutes or until edges are lightly brown.

title: divinity
directions: In a heavy 3 quart saucepan, bring sugar, Karo, water and salt to boil until hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then gradually beat in boiling syrup.
Beat until stiff.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat again.
Pour onto a greased platter.
Cut when cool.

title: scalloped spinach
directions: Add all ingredients to spinach, except bread crumbs.
Mix together and pour into a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: a good dish for potlucks
directions: Cook first three ingredients for an hour or so, add Polish sausage (sliced or in pieces).
Continue simmering for additional half hour or so.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add chopped onion and saute. Add soup, milk, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Add to rice mixture after draining well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine meat and sauce.
Layer sauce, uncooked lasagna noodles, sauce and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Continue until finished, ending with sauce and cheese. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O with 3 cups water (2 hot and 1 cold).
Add crushed pineapple with juice; add blueberry pie filling.
Chill until firm.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Chill.

title: old fashioned pie crust
directions: Blend lard and flour.
Add water, mix and knead.
Makes crust for 3 pies.

title: tex mex bean dip
directions: Mash 1 avocado with lemon juice and mix with avocado dip.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix in a separate bowl.
Mix bean dip, beans, garlic and Tabasco.
Spread in a clear glass dish.
Top with avocado mixture; spread sour cream mixture evenly over avocado mixture.
Sprinkle sour cream with green onions.
Spread tomatoes over top.
Then layer on the olives.
Cover with Cheddar cheese. Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in skillet as you would batter cakes.

title: marinated broccoli salad
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil, cool completely.
Can be served immediately or refrigerated for a few days.

title: christmas boil
directions: Cut lemon and orange peel in small pieces.
Add water and simmer on stove or in potpourri pot.
Add water as mixture evaporates.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Cream together in a large bowl the brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and butter.
Add 2 cups flour and vanilla.
Mix dates with 3 tablespoons of flour in small bowl and toss.
Add dates and pecan pieces.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: honey roasted almonds
directions: Spread the almonds in a single layer in a shallow ungreased baking pan and place in cold oven.
Bake at 350°, stirring occasionally, until the internal color of the nuts is tan to light brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
(The nuts will continue to roast a little more after they are removed from the oven.)
Set the roasted almonds aside.
Thoroughly mix the sugar and salt.
Stir together the honey, water and oil in a medium-size saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir in the roasted almonds and continue to cook and stir until all of the liquid has been absorbed by the nuts, about 5 minutes.
Immediately transfer the almonds to a medium-size bowl into which some sugar mixture has been sprinkled. Sprinkle the remaining sugar mixture over the almonds and toss until they are evenly coated.
Spread the almonds out on wax paper. When cool, store at room temperature in a tightly covered container or plastic bag for up to 2 weeks.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hot zesty chip dip
directions: Pan-fry ground beef and hot sausage; drain to remove oil.
Then add cream of mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz, peppers (diced) and juice. Let cook until cheese melts and blends together.
Ready to serve.

title: double baked potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, salt and mashed potatoes.
Add butter, milk and 8 ounces cream cheese.
Add paprika on top.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt and oregano.
Stir in flour and tomatoes
and
simmer
10 minutes.	Cook noodles in salt water and drain.
Layer noodles and hamburger alternately in casserole. Layer
cheese
over
all
and
sprinkle
with
Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: green beans in mustard sauce
directions: Blanch green beans in a pot of boiling salted water (6 minutes).
Drain and set aside.
Mix the remaining ingredients and blend well.
Add the drained beans.
Toss and serve hot.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Add vanilla and eggs one at at time; beat after each. Make paste of coloring and cocoa; add to batter. Add rest of ingredients alternately, dry and liquid. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Run peppers through blender with vinegar.
Pour into boiler. Add sugar.
Stir to dissolve and bring to a boil.
Add Certo and bring to a boil again.
Skim off foam.
Do not strain.
Put in jars and seal.
This is good with meats.

title: potato salad
directions: Place potatoes and onions in bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix lightly with French dressing.
Chill an hour or two.

title: banana bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, vanilla and bananas. Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.

title: easy cabbage dish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large skillet.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Yield: About 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion and chilies in butter.
Add chicken, then add milk and soups.
Layer crumbled Doritos, mixture, more Doritos and Cheddar cheese.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise and remove yolks into a small bowl and mash well.
Stir in milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Fill hollowed egg halves with mixture and serve.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix with apples in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with water.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Saute
chicken	for
about
5 minutes in oil or butter. Remove from pan.
Saute onion, tomato, green pepper and celery in	same oil or butter.
Add rice and mix.
Cover these ingredients with boiling water.
Add bay leaf, thyme, parsley, salt and
pepper. Add
chicken.
Simmer
until chicken is soft and tender.
Add ham.
Season to taste.
Dry out the jambalaya by placing in oven for 5 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: yogurt-poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Yields 1/2 cup.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and cream together with other two cheeses. Add and mix well the red wine vinegar and garlic powder.
Roll into ball.
Cover well with parsley and pecans.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: lumpia shanghai
directions: In a skillet, brown ground pork for 15 minutes, then ground beef for 10 minutes.
Drain fat, add shrimp, onions, egg, salt, soy sauce, water chestnuts, pepper, carrots, m.s.g. and mix well. Separate wrapper and spoon about 3 tablespoons mixture into each wrapper and roll tightly.
Brush end of wrapper with water to seal. Heat oil in a deep fryer or skillet.
Fry "rolls" until golden brown.
Cut roll into 2 pieces.
Serve hot with sweet and sour sauce.

title: mustard-glazed ham
directions: Cut rind of ham, if present.
Score top surface of ham; stud with cloves.
Place, fat side up, on a rack in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven approximately 15 minutes per pound, or follow wrapper directions.
Combine sugar, syrup and mustard.
Use 3/4 cup of glaze to baste ham every 10 minutes during the last 30 to 45 minutes of baking.
Stir cornstarch into remaining glaze in saucepan.
Add pineapple with juice.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Serve sauce with ham.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender.
Serve with chips and crackers.
(You may use a small sour cream in place of mayonnaise.)

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine water chestnuts, mushrooms, onions and 2 tablespoons dressing.
Divide vegetable mixture into 4 equal portions and place on top of chicken pieces. Roll up.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: cherry delight
directions: Spoon stir the Eagle Brand into Cool Whip. Slowly stir in lemon juice.
Add drained cherries and pecan pieces. Stir and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate.

title: pit barbeque sauce
directions: Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Add onions and garlic and saute until onion is tender. Add all other ingredients and bring to boil. Reduce to simmer, and cook until slightly thicken. Remove from heat and let cool. Use as basting sauce.

title: batter-for-anything
directions: Combine cooking oil and egg; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.

title: chicken crunch
directions: In shallow dish, combine 1/3 cup soup and 1/4 cup milk and set aside.
On waxed paper, spread flour and dip chicken breasts into it.
Then dip into soup mixture and then place in Pyrex baking dish, dribble with margarine and cook 20 minutes at 400°.
In saucepan, mix rest of soup, 1/4 cup milk, parsley and lemon juice. Stir over low heat.
Pour sauce over chicken when serving.

title: chicken pasta
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salt water.
Drain well.
In a sauce pan on medium heat, add cubed chicken, mushrooms, Alfredo sauce, frozen vegetables and milk.
Cook until heated.
Serve sauce over cooked pasta.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake and cool cake layers.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and refrigerate to set.
Place 1 cake layer in bottom of 6-quart punch bowl.
Add in layers, halving in this order:
pudding, cherry pie filling, fruit cocktail, pineapple, nuts, coconut and whipped topping.
Repeat with other half in same order.
Can garnish with cherries, nuts and coconut.
May be made in advance.

title: chicken wings marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread slices.
Butter both sides with margarine and line bottom of 10 x 14-inch casserole.
Brown bacon and crumble over top of bread layer.
Grate cheeses and mix together.
Sprinkle cheeses lightly over bacon layer in casserole (do not press down).
Beat together eggs, salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce and milk.
Carefully pour over cheeses in casserole. Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Gradually add confectioners sugar and mix.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate bits in a double boiler and pour over mixture.
Chill and cut into small squares.

title: whole roast lemon chicken with vegetables
directions: Pat insides and outsides of chickens dry, discarding excess fat.
Using a two-tined fork, pierce the lemons at 1/4-inch intervals.
Place a lemon in the cavity of each chicken and close the cavity with metal skewers.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
In separate bowl, mix soup, milk and sauce. Alternate layers of Fritos, meat sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chex mix
directions: Combine cereals, nuts and pretzels in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
Stir together margarine, garlic salt, onion salt, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce; gently stir mixture over cereal, nuts and pretzels until well coated.
Bake at 250° for about 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool. Store in airtight container.
Yields 9 cups.

title: famous snug restaurant cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add whipping cream and beat well.
Add milk and beat more.
Makes 2 pies.
Bake slowly at 300°.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease or spray Pam into pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high
or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: hot triscuit hors d' oeuvres
directions: In bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Spread on Triscuits. Bake in a 350° oven for 5 to 7 minutes or heat in Medium temperature microwave until cheese mixture barely melts.
Serve hot.
Cheese mixture may be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: kornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add milk, well beaten eggs and lard.
Bake in greased cast-iron skillet about 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chops to taste.
Brown chops in butter.
Saute onions, celery and bell pepper.
Add soup, water and rice.
Pour all ingredients in casserole dish.
Place chops on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup, beef, crumbs, onion, Worcestershire, egg and pepper in 2-quart oblong baking dish.
Shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Spoon off fat; reserve 1 to 2 tablespoons drippings.

title: party tortilla rolls
directions: Blend all ingredients (except tortillas) in a food processor. Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Cut into 1-inch pieces and serve.

title: aunt lee's mushroom quiche
directions: Beat the eggs.
Mix in salt and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 325° with a glass dish, 350° with a metal pan. Quiche is done when a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: indian beans
directions: Wash beans, place in 6-quart kettle with 3 quarts water and bring to simmer.
Cover.
Cook 4 hours or until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients with beans and cooking water.
Place in 4-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 2 to 3 hours, or until done.
Add water, if necessary.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sundown cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Mix all ingredients (except fruit). Pour into baking dish; top with fruit and sprinkle top with sugar. Bake at 350° till golden brown.

title: bumble bee bread
directions: Cook brown sugar and butter until shiny (approximately 1 minute).
Cut up biscuits and put in buttered pan.
Pour sauce over biscuits and bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: slim scampi-style shrimp on skewers
directions: Carefully shell, clean and devein shrimp.
(Butterfly, if desired.)
Combine in plastic bag with remaining ingredients (except parsley and lemon).
Drain shrimp and thread on skewers; reserve marinade.
Broil or barbecue shrimp, 4 to 5-inches from heat source for about 2 minutes each side, until pinkish and opaque.
Brush with reserved marinade after turning.
If desired, garnish with parsley and lemon.
Makes 4 servings; about 160 calories each.

title: hidden valley ranch meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef and salad dressing mix; shape into meatballs.
Melt margarine in a skillet and brown meatballs on all sides.
Add broth, cover and simmer until cooked.
Serve warm with toothpicks.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: peach jam
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan, mash peaches and stir in the pectin. Bring to a boil and boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add honey and lemon juice.
Bring to a full boil and boil hard for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Skim off the foam.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes four 1/2 pints.

title: zucchini rich rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, yeast and salt.
Mix well. In a saucepan heat zucchini, milk, water and oil until 125° (use candy thermometer).
Then add liquid mixture, then the egg.
Blend at low speed on electric mixer, enough to get a smooth mixture. Then continue to stir in rest of dry ingredients, using a wooden spoon.
Makes a sticky dough, but knead a few times.
Cover and let rise until double in a warm place, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and divide into 24 pieces, forming into balls with fingers moistened with shortening.
Place in greased round 8-inch pans. Cover and let rise 45 minutes, covered.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the pie filling together.
Spread 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over batter.
Spread remaining batter over pie filling.
Sprinkle a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Good warm or cold.

title: chickpea salad
directions: In a bowl, mix together peas, onion and tomato.
Into a jar measure corn oil, vinegar, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper. Cover tightly and shake well.
Pour over vegetables; toss.

title: beef or pork barbecue
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve on hot dog or hamburger bun.

title: *cornbread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sour milk, sugar and salt; mix.
Add flour, corn meal, baking powder and soda; stir.
Add shortening and bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: best hash browns in the world
directions: Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Add all ingredients. Cook and turn to desired doneness.
(Hotter heat for fast browning.)
Add more margarine if potatoes absorb all the margarine.

title: chestnut stuffing
directions: Shell and blanch chestnuts; cook in boiling water until tender.
While still hot, rub them through a sieve.
Add the other ingredients.

title: colache
directions: Peel tomatoes; remove seeds and dice.
Chop squash.
Scrape corn from cobs.
Heat oleo in large skillet.
Add onion; cook 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and cook on low 15 to 20 minutes, stirring now and then.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with topping.

title: rotelle with artichokes and red peppers
directions: Cook rotelle according to package instructions.
Heat olive oil in pan.
When hot, add garlic and cook until golden.
Add red peppers.
Cook until still crunchy.
Add tomatoes; cook 2 minutes. Add artichoke hearts.
Cook until heated.
Stir in basil, oregano and wine vinegar.
Combine with cooked pasta.
Stir in grated cheese.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon, flour, oats, salt and melted butter. Put on top of the apples. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Examine sourwood blooms for dirt and insects. Remove leaves. Pack a 1-quart bowl full of blooms and pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over them. Cover at once.
Let stand not over 1 minute. Drain and strain through a cloth. Add 1 1/2 cups sugar for each cup of water.
To 6 cups of the water after it has begun to thicken (after cooking slowly), add a small piece of alum about the size of a dime. Crush alum.
Thicken to desired texture, letting it boil down.

title: eddie's famous wacky cake
directions: In an ungreased 8-inch square pan, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, mix together oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Make 3 indentations in the flour mixture and pour the oil mixture evenly into them.
Pour cold water over top of it all and stir until smooth.
(Be sure to mix well in the corners.)
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until tester comes out clean.

title: pan-fried cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, butter and dates.
Cook in skillet, about 8 minutes over low heat, stirring constantly.
Take off stove and add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Let cool; form in balls and roll in coconut.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies and mix with butter.
Use 2/3 of mixture to pat onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut ice cream into slices and place over cookie crust.
Pour topping over ice cream.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining cookie mix over top.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Thaw 15 minutes before serving.

title: frosted strawberry squares
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in 3 cups boiling water. Immediately add frozen strawberries, stirring until completely thawed.
Pour into lightly oiled 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until partially set.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in reserved juice.
Place cream cheese in blender.
Add hot lemon gelatin.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over strawberry gelatin.
Chill until set.

title: goat cheese torta
directions: Line a 2 to 3-cup bowl with plastic wrap. Combine goat cheese, cream cheese and garlic in a bowl; mix well. Season with salt and pepper. Spoon half of the cheese mixture into a prepared bowl. Spread with tomatoes. Spread with Pesto. Spoon half of the remaining cheese mixture over the pesto. (Sprinkle cheese mixture over the pesto.) Chill, covered with plastic wrap, for 2 to 6 hours. Invert onto a serving platter. Garnish with fresh herbs. Serve with baguette slices. Store leftovers in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add baking powder, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in pecans and graham crackers.
Pour into buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes its own crust as it bakes.

title: celery-apple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add cinnamon candies to 1/2 cup boiling water; stir to dissolve.
Add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Add to dissolved Jell-O.
Cool until partially set. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart mold or 6 individual molds; chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl and stir to mix thoroughly.
Cook as you would for any standard pancake recipe. Serve with maple syrup.

title: birdnest cookies
directions: Melt chocolate; stir in noodles and cornflakes.
Drop on wax paper using a teaspoon.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Bake in 9 or 10-inch tube pan at 325° for about 80 minutes.
Do not use Bundt pan.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together and pack in 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday brew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Serve.

title: brunswick stew(yields 16 servings)
directions: Slice salt pork down to the skin and put in the pot with other meats.
Put in salt; simmer until meat separates from the bones, about 3 hours.
Remove meat from bones and add to all the vegetables.
Mix well and add seasoning.
Put on very low heat until it begins to cook and then let simmer barely.
Stir often to prevent sticking.
Stew is ready when thick and mushy.
Add seasoning to taste.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add the sherbet and oranges.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Split Twinkies and place cream down and pour jello mixture over Twinkies.
Refrigerate.
Also very good with a few pecan pieces in it and used as a salad, omitting the Twinkies.

title: real mexican enchilada casserole
directions: Empty all enchilada sauce into a bowl for dipping shells.
Dip the corn tortilla shells (6) into sauce.
Place flat on bottom of 14 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle layer of cooked ground beef, layer of chopped onion and a layer of grated cheese.
Dip remaining 6 shells and repeat layers.
If there is any extra sauce, it may be poured over casserole.
Cover with foil; bake in preheated oven at 400° for approximately 45 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: red rice
directions: Crumble bacon; set aside.
In small skillet in 2 tablespoons oil, cook chopped onion, green pepper, tomatoes and garlic about 5 minutes or until onion and pepper are tender.
Add with crumbled bacon, some chopped parsley and a few slivers pimiento to 2 cups hot cooked rice.
Toss to blend well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, Cool Whip, sour cream and sugar. Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Put fruit topping over top.

title: mini drumsticks
directions: Marinate at least 2 hours in soy sauce, sugars, vinegar, ginger, garlic and broth.
Keep turning.
Take drumsticks out of marinade and put in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baste often.
Serve crisp.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Golden fry onions in butter.
Beat eggs and add all ingredients except 2 slices of Swiss cheese for top of pie to melt.
Bake in 350° oven until brown on top (approximately 25 to 30 minutes).

title: honey-nut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
In a medium bowl, beat butter and brown sugar 5 to 8 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat until blended.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt into a medium bowl.
Stir flour mixture into egg mixture alternately with milk, stirring until combined.
Fold in chopped nuts.

title: royal french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake well.

title: onion casserole(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Slice onions; place in bottom of casserole dish. Cook sausage; drain and sprinkle on top of onion slices. Crush crackers on top of this. Spoon mushroom soup on top. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until onions are clear.

title: old fashioned pulled mints
directions: Boil the water and add to sugar and softened butter. Boil until mixture spins a thread (hard crack stage).
Pour out on a greased slab of marble. Add the oil of peppermint and food coloring. Let cool only long enough so that you can pick it up with greased fingers. (Candy will still be hot.)
Work fast by pulling as for taffy. When candy toughens and starts turning silvery, twist and cut with scissors.
Put cool mints in can containers and they will "cream" overnight.

title: helen's delight chocolate cake
directions: Mix together sugar and flour in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, bring butter, shortening, cocoa and water to a boil.
Pour mixture over the flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add soda, buttermilk, cinnamon, vanilla, eggs and a dash of salt.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400° in greased shallow pan.

title: coconut muffins
directions: Grease and lightly flour 6 muffin cups.
In small bowl, stir flour and salt.
In another bowl, beat butter or margarine for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and almond extract; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and beat mixture for 1 minute.
Add flour mixture to beaten mixture.
Stir in toasted coconut.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on cooled muffins.
Yields 6.

title: ham tetrazzini
directions: In medium saucepan, saute ham in butter about 2 minutes; remove.
Saute mushrooms; remove.
Saute onion until tender; blend in flour.
Gradually add broth and half and half.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until sauce thickens.
Add Swiss cheese, mustard, pepper and sherry.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add ham and mushrooms.
Combine with spaghetti in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
If desired, sprinkle with toasted slivered almonds.
When ready to serve, broil 3 to 4 inches from broiler until lightly browned.
Serves 6.
You can double this recipe for 10 to 12 servings.

title: apricot glazed pork roast(crock pot)
directions: Mix broth, preserves, onion and mustard in slow cooker.
Add pork and turn to coat.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 8 hours. If you wish to have shredded pork, just cook longer.

title: raisin bar cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water for 6 minutes; set aside. Cream shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add raisins (water and all), 2 cups flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli pie
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in oil until tender, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to a large bowl; add eggs, broccoli, cheese, salt and nutmeg.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs slightly and add to sugar. Add other ingredients.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° about 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients, on top of stove, until thick, then add blueberries and lemon juice.

title: beach slaw
directions: Mix first four ingredients and set aside.

title: tomato bisque
directions: Put tomatoes in stew pan.
Stir in baking soda.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Add milk and sugar.
Stir all together and heat.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter with powdered sugar until mealy.
Sprinkle 2/3 of mixture on pie shell.

title: nut crackers
directions: Make a paste of oleo, brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Spread each cracker; put on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 6 minutes. Remove immediately and put on wax paper.
When cool, sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: potatoes and chicken dijon
directions: Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick and microwave 8 to 10 minutes until tender.
In large skillet, toss and brown chicken in oil over high heat 5 minutes.
Add potatoes; saute and toss until potatoes are light brown.
Add barbecue sauce and tarragon.
Heat until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: venison and lentils
directions: Simmer ingredients for 1 1/2 hours.
Add slices of venison steak and simmer for 1 1/2 hours more.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs, then coconut, then chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Then spread milk over and press nuts lightly into mix.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes; cut into bars.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine onion soup with the boiling water and cream of chicken soup. Stir into rice in baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Cover dish lightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: fruit faces
directions: To perk up a party or turn lunch or snack into a fun filled, hour long project, simply provide paper plates, finger foods as shown (or others) and allow children to create edible characters.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, eggs, onion, seasonings and crumbs.
Mix well. Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Serves 6.

title: pistachio salad
