directions: Mix pineapple and pistachio pudding.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts (optional).
Chill and serve.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl; mix thoroughly.
Spoon into well-greased muffin pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen large rolls.
Delicious and easy!

title: baked pork and sweet potatoes
directions: Place pork in
a
shallow
pan.
Add sweet potatoes and cover with honey and orange juice.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hearty turkey-apple toss
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over turkey and apple.
Add celery, eggs, almonds and seasonings.
Fold into turkey mixture.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Garnish with apple wedges.

title: louise's broccoli salad
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients and toss over broccoli.
Mix about 30 minutes before serving.
Reserve 3 slices bacon to crumble on top.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: In large bowl combine cornbread muffin mix, beaten eggs, cottage cheese, thawed broccoli, chopped onion and garlic powder. Mix well.
Add melted margarine and mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: poor man's lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomato sauce and spices; put aside.
Cook noodles; drain.
Pour noodles in a 9-inch baking dish. Mix cream cheese and sour cream together, then mix with noodles. Pour tomato sauce-ground beef mixture over noodles, then sprinkle sharp cheese over top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add crumbs and milk.
Beat until smooth and add vanilla, then beat again.
Fold in coconut, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into oiled, 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon cucumber pickle rings(the merilwood farm of harold and marion pittman, hernando)
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers into 1/3 inch thick.
Then carefully cut out rounded centers.
Soak the cucumber rings in 2 cups of lime and 8 1/2 quarts of water for 24 hours.
After 24 hours, drain and wash.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla together until blended and fluffy.
Whip cream until soft peaks form.
Stir half of whipped cream into peanut butter mixture until smooth. Fold in remaining whipped cream until blended.
Smooth mixture into premade crust.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
In small saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Drizzle over pie and refrigerate until firm.

title: cold macaroni salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except macaroni.
Mix together with macaroni and chill.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar slowly, and beat until fluffy. Beat eggs; blend into butter mixture.
Measure flour.
Chop fruits and nuts and mix with part of flour.
Sift together remaining flour and baking powder.
Add flavoring and fold into the egg-butter mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased, paper lined tube pan.
Place in cold oven, set oven controls at 250° and bake for 3 hours.

title: oatmeal crunchies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla. Beat well; stir in oats and nuts and form into balls.
Dip top into granulated sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken. Dice and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic; set aside.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel together.
Add onion, garlic and chicken.
Mix well.
Line 9 1/2 x 11-inch pan with chips.
Next, add chicken mixture.
Then add a layer of cheeses.
Continue layering, ending with cheeses.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with leftover tostada chips.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until thick.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Freeze in a one gallon, hand-cranked ice cream freezer.
Take turns cranking.
Put a stack of newspapers on top of the freezer and let young 'uns take turns sitting on it to hold it steady.
Once ice cream is stiff, pour off brine.
Remove dasher from freezer and let the young 'uns fight over who gets to lick it.
If you can stand the wait, pack down the cream, cover with wax paper and re-seal.
Re-pack freezer with layers of ice and rock salt.
Wait as long as you can (up to an hour).
Dish out and serve.
Makes 1 gallon.
Serves 8 to 12 regular folks or 3 to 4 Williamses.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate for one hour.

title: judy's banana ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar in a large bowl and beat well.
Add creams and vanilla and mix well.
Stir in bananas until well blended. Pour mixture into 4-quart ice cream freezer and freeze as usual.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Mix the sugar, mayonnaise and milk together; pour over salad and toss.
Chill.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Line 11x13 cake pan with mixture. Bake at 400 for 6 min. Let cool.

title: zesty veggies
directions: In a large frypan, mix the first 6 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Simmer 5 minutes. Cool. Refrigerate in tightly covered container at least 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken pieces, soup and vegetables.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with biscuits.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until biscuits are brown and mixture is bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Cut cake into thin slices.
Divide slices into 3 pieces each. Set aside.

title: baked ham
directions: Prick ham with tiny holes and marinate in sauce overnight. Keep in refrigerator.
Pour sauce off ham and save to baste while cooking.
Place ham in 325° oven and baste with sauce occasionally until done.

title: pam's english pea salad
directions: Drain peas and carrots.
Add onion, mayonnaise and cubed cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: irene's tomatoes
directions: Mix Italian dressing according to package directions.
Slice tomatoes and arrange them flat in a shallow dish.
Sprinkle dill and parsley over the top, then the dressing and refrigerate.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients at low speed with mixer. Spoon into 3 graham cracker crusts. Chill.

title: fresh banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 12 cup Bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In a large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and 1/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla, bananas and buttermilk until well combined.

title: fried banana peppers
directions: Use as many banana peppers as you need for your family. Cut off end. Pull out seeds. Stuff with grated Mozzarella cheese. Make batter.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mince shrimp, onion and pickles.
Mix with other ingredients and serve with crackers.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: First
layer:
Combine	flour,	butter, sugar, salt and 1/2 cup pecans.
Press into
a	9 x 13-inch pan; bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: potato bacon frittata
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until browned.
Remove and drain; reserve none but 4 tablespoons bacon fat.
Cook spuds, onion, green pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt in bacon fat until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in bacon. Beat together eggs, cheese, milk, baking mix, butter and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour egg mixture into greased quiche dish or 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spoon potato mixture on top of eggs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, until set.
Remove Frittata from oven.

title: coca-cola classic roast brisket(aka awesome saucesome)
directions: Preheat a large heavy skillet.
Add oil and brown brisket on both sides.
Lay brisket in the bottom of a slow cooker (crock-pot).
Sprinkle top with salt, pepper and garlic.
Combine cola, chili sauce, Worcestershire and horseradish.
Pour over roast.
Cover and cook on low for 9 to 11 hours (high 5 to 6 hours).
If cooking in the oven, bake at 325°, wrapped in foil, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Slice brisket thinly on the diagonal and serve with sauce spooned over it.

title: butterscotch drop cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar for five minutes at medium speed. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Combine dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Add nuts and mix well.
Chill dough until firm and then drop on greased baking sheets.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: oat bran pizza
directions: Mix flour, oat bran and salt in medium bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water in a measuring cup.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil. Stir until dissolved.
Add to flour mixture and stir to form dough.

title: jewish fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon;
marinate. In large bowl combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Beat until creamy. Add vanilla and orange juice, beating until well blended.
Add flour, baking
powder
and
salt, beating until well blended. Grease and flour a tube pan.
Place layer of marinated apples in pan
and cover
with half of batter.
Add another layer of apples
and remaining batter.
Top with apple slices.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Prepare cake as directed on the box or use
your
own scratch recipe.
Before pouring cake mix into cake pan,
add
cup sauerkraut to cake mix; stir thoroughly.	Pour cake
into cake pan and bake as required on box. Allow cake to cool
thoroughly
after removing from the oven. Frost with chocolate
frosting.
Sauerkraut
is
not
noticed except seeing it in the cake.
The taste does not exist.	Your cake will be very moist.

title: creamed cabbage slaw
directions: *Can use nonfat or regular milk by adding a little of cider vinegar prior to adding milk, so it sours.

title: calavositas
directions: Brown meat and drain completely.
Add onions, squash, corn and seasonings.
Cook until onion and squash are slightly tender.
Add green chilies.
Sprinkle cheese on top and let melt.
Spoon meat mixture in flour tortillas and serve.

title: pumpkin crunch pudding cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, lined with waxed paper.
Sprinkle the box of dry cake mix on top of pumpkin mixture.
Pat nuts on top.
Spoon the cooled, melted butter over nuts evenly.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool and then invert onto a large tray.

title: laverne's layered look
directions: Mix together.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: mama's meat balls and gravy
directions: Combine the ground beef, chopped onion, 3 tablespoon parsley, beaten egg, bread, salt and pepper to taste and pinch of nutmeg; shape into 1 1/2-inch meat balls.
Brown in oil.
Add beef broth and chicken broth; simmer 30 minutes.
Remove and strain broth. Return 1/2 cup broth to skillet and whisk in the flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Slowly whisk in remaining broth, grated lemon peel and thyme.
Add meat balls and simmer for 5 minutes more.
Garnish with parsley and serve over mashed potatoes or wide noodles.

title: quiche(anytime dish)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fry sausage, green pepper and onion. Drain.
Combine cheese and flour. Stir in sausage, green pepper and onion.
Pour in shell.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over cheese and sausage.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan log rolls
directions: Stir marshmallow cream, sugar and vanilla. Form into rolls with the palms of your hands. Allow to harden for awhile in the refrigerator. The rolls should be about 5 inches long and 2 1/2 inches in diameter. Makes 10 to 12 centers.

title: bacon lettuce salad
directions: Shred lettuce and onion into bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp. Lift out with slotted spoon and add to lettuce.
Pour bacon drippings from pan, then
return 2 tablespoons.
Stir in remaining ingredients, heat to boiling, then cool to warm.
Drizzle over lettuce.
Toss to mix well.
Delicious.

title: anybody can do yogurt pie(serves 8)
directions: Fold yogurt into Cool Whip (thawed).
Spoon into graham cracker pie crust.
Freeze until firm (about 4 hours).
Remove from freezer at least 30 minutes before serving and keep cold in refrigerator.
Garnish with strawberries, blueberries or lemon slices.

title: zesty sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill.
Serve with fish, chicken or shrimp, or as a sandwich spread.
Yields 2 cups.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In 8 cups water in large pot on high heat, add the Lipton mix and beef cubes.
Cook hamburg in frying pan.
Place into soup. Add mixed vegetables and V-8 juice; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add seasonings; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: cindy's four layer torte
directions: Blend together flour, 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar, walnuts and margarine.
Press in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool.
Blend cream cheese and 1 cup confectioners sugar until smooth.
Fold in 9 ounce Cool Whip.
Spread on first layer.
Chill. Mix pudding and milk according to package instructions.
Spread on second layer.
Chill.
Top with 9 ounce Cool Whip and sprinkle with some chopped walnuts.

title: crock-pot swiss steak
directions: Coat steak with seasoned flour.
Brown in oil in
skillet. Place in crock-pot with remaining ingredients.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Cook on low for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: homemade ice cream for 5-quart freezer
directions: Use a large can of crushed pineapple with vanilla mix for pineapple flavor.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage; drain and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and serve in crock pot.

title: chocolate chip applesauce cake
directions: On slow speed, cream the margarine with the sugar. Add eggs. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with applesauce.
Mix in 1/2 cup nuts.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased). Sprinkle top of unbaked cake with mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bob's fish couvillion
directions: Cook fish in water (boil 15 minutes).
Saute onion, garlic, bell pepper and celery in oil.
Add flour to sauteed vegetables and brown lightly.
Add to fish and water.
Add V-8 juice, tomato paste, Ro-Tel tomatoes with juice, Worcestershire and Tony's.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook covered on low for approximately 1 hour. If using shrimp, add to couvillion the last 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: greek pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. On floured surface, roll out pizza dough to fit either a pizza pan or a pizza stone. Put 1 teaspoon olive oil on pan and spread it with paper towel. Take pizza dough and place it in pan, then put 1 teaspoon olive oil on top of dough and spread with paper towel or brush. Spread minced galic, then break up spinach and place on top of garlic, then put Feta cheese on top of spinach. Cut tomato into wedges and place them evenly over pizza. Top off with Mozzarella cheese. Place in 400° oven for around 25 minutes. Cook until cheese is a little golden brown.

title: stroganoff meatballs
directions: Combine chuck, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper and parsley. Shape into meatballs and cook in skillet, turning after 1/2 hour for a total of 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Partly cook meat and onion. Add to batter and cook in moderate oven. Best cooked in iron skillet.

title: microwaved carrots
directions: Slice peeled carrots 1/4-inch thick; put into 1-quart casserole with water.
Cover; cook on High for 7 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes; drain.
Add rest of ingredients; mix and serve.

title: parmesan herb bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread on bread.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with Italian pasta meal.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan at 350° for one hour.

title: parmesan breadsticks
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
In a pie plate, beat egg, salt and pepper.
Dip breadsticks, one at a time, into mixture and then in Parmesan cheese.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 7 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 1 1/4 cups sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in sweet potatoes and milk.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg; add to creamed mixture, stirring just until moistened. Stir in raisins and pecans.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 22 to 25 minutes.

title: corn flake bars
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugars and syrup over low heat.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and stir well.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together corn flakes and peanuts; stir in sugar-syrup mixture, mixing well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and press firmly.
Melt chips and spread on top.
Cut into squares all the way through and refrigerate.
Cool and break into squares. Remember, cut while warm!

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pears au chocolat
directions: Peel pears.
Combine sugar and water in medium saucepan. Simmer for 10 to 20 minutes or until soft.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool pears.
Pour chocolate sauce on pears.

title: weight watchers frozen snickers
directions: Mix together and freeze in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix and pour over boned chicken pieces.
Marinate 30 minutes or overnight.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine carrot, apple and onion in a bowl; toss gently.
Set aside.
Combine oil, juice, vinegar, salt and ginger, stirring well.
Pour dressing over carrot mixture; toss gently.
Cover and chill.
Add pecans and toss gently just before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: crispy refrigerator pickles
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, salt and seed just to a boil to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat and add cucumbers and onions.
Cool. Transfer to containers; seal.
Refrigerate 24 hours to 1 month.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple to boiling point.
Remove from heat; add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Fold in buttermilk, pecans and Cool Whip.
Pour into mold or 2-quart casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Refrigerate until congealed.
Serve on lettuce for salad.

title: scratch brownies surprise
directions: Mix cake flour, baking powder and salt together.
Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, corn oil and vanilla in a separate bowl.
Slowly add sugar.
Melt chocolate slowly and add to mixture.
Stir in dry ingredients and nuts to wet mixture.
Put in 13 x 9-inch greased baking pan.
Bake for 32 to 35 minutes and test for continuity. Cut in squares while warm.
Should yield 24 brownies.
Serve with warm cherries on top.

title: granddad's buttermilk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add eggs and buttermilk (with soda dissolved in it).
Beat 2 minutes, then add extracts.
Bake in angel food cake pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Place oil, sugar and eggs in a large bowl and mix.
Add flour which has been sifted together with all the spices, salt and soda. Add applesauce, raisins and pecans; stir.
Pour batter in a greased tube or bundt pan and bake 2 hours and 15 minutes at 250 degrees.

title: flowerpot dirt cake
directions: You will also need an 8-inch flowerpot, trowel and silk flowers.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Blend potato soup until smooth, add chicken broth and salt. Gently stir in half and half.
Chill; add chives on top when served.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Cream butter in large bowl.
Add sugar gradually; mix.
Add egg; mix.
Add sifted dry ingredients (except sugar and cinnamon). Roll dough into balls; roll each one in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: egg breakfast sausage
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Cover with wax paper.
Bake at 350° the next morning for 45 minutes. You must refrigerate overnight.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Season crawfish tails with salt and pepper and set aside.
Melt margarine in a heavy pot; add onions, bell peppers, celery and garlic, and cook over low heat until done.
Add crawfish, fat, and 4 cups of water.
Bring to a boil, and add more water to cover crawfish tails.
Bring to a second boil, cover and cook another 15 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water and add.
Add green onions and parsley and cook another 10 minutes.
Serve over rice. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli-raisin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: portuguese kale soup
directions: In large pot place beef, chorizo and peas.
Add enough water to cover, cook until peas are almost done.
Add cabbage, kale and potatoes.
When potatoes are cooked, remove from stove.
Season with salt and pepper.
This is delicious and is a good, hearty soup.

title: strawberry angel food delight
directions: Pinch cake into bite-size chunks, place in 13 x 9-inch pan. In separate bowl, mix Jell-O with boiling water (follow directions on package).
Pour Jell-O mixture over entire cake.
In separate bowl mix yogurt and Cool Whip.
Spread yogurt mixture over cake and Jell-O.
Freeze 4 hours.
Set out 30 minutes before serving.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Add eggs and fruit with juice.
Pour into 2 cake pans.
Sprinkle top of both layers with brown sugar and cover with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Place cabbage leaves in boiling water to cover.
Set aside. In small saucepan, melt 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add the chopped onion and cook until golden brown.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the browned onion, egg, milk and bread crumbs.
Mix well and allow bread crumbs to soften, about 5 minutes.
Stir in beef, salt and pepper and mix well.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Add sugar, eggs and flour.
Add nuts and vanilla. Bake in square pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Suitable for freezing.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Slice round steak into 1/4-inch strips.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook until tender (about 8 hours) or can be baked at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudgy pecan pie
directions: Line unpricked pastry shell with a double thickness of heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 450 degrees for 5 minutes.
Remove foil and set shell aside.
Reduce heat to 375 degrees.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat yolks slightly; add sugar and beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla, chocolate and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into deep 9-inch pie plate lined with pastry.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°, then 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool, then cover with whipped cream.

title: tangy sour cream(low-calorie)
directions: Place ingredients in blender or work bowl of a food processor fitted with a metal blade.
Process until completely smooth.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Mixture may be thinned with skim milk, if desired.
Makes approximately 1 2/3 cups.
Serves 28; 1 tablespoon per serving.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Set aside.
Place half cornbread in bottom of large dish.
Top with half of beans.
In a medium bowl, combine tomatoes, onion and pepper.
Layer half of mixture over beans.
Layer half of cheese, bacon, corn and reserved salad dressing.
Repeat layers using remaining ingredients.
Garnish as desired.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray the bottom of a 13x9 pan with non-stick cooking spray. Place bread on the bottom of pan. Sprinkle cheddar cheese, sausage, Jack cheese, green chile. Pour egg, milk and seasoning mixture over layers. Allow to set overnight.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients.
Beat eggs in 1 cup warm water; set aside.
Blend the yeast in 1 cup warm water; set aside.
Mix all together.
Divide dough.
Roll each section to a 9-inch circle.
Cut each circle in 12 wedge shape pieces.
Roll each wedge, starting with wide end and rolling to point.
Arrange rolls, point down, on greased cookie sheet.
Curve each slightly. Bake immediately at 400°.

title: lena's old fashion cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; dice tomato, cucumber and carrot.
Mix all other ingredients together with the cabbage, tomato, cucumbers and carrot.
Now it's ready to eat.

title: shrimp enchiladas
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan.
Add onions and saute. Add shrimp; cook until shrimp are pink.
Then add green chilies and half of pimentos.
Add soup and cream cheese until melted. Let cool.
Put 1/3 to 1/2 of cup in center of tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in 9 x 13-inch oiled baking dish.
Top with rest of sauce, pimentos and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and break into pieces.
Brown sausage with green peppers and onions.
Drain excess fat.
Combine all ingredients. Cook for 5 hours at 250°.

title: homemade baby wipes
directions: Cut roll of paper towels in half.
Put 1/2 roll into plastic bowl with liquid ingredients.
Put on lid.
Allow all liquid ingredients to be absorbed, about 1 hour.
Then pull out center cardboard tube to start to use wipes.
Store in bowl.

title: giant polka dot cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in egg, then water.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in oats.
On greased cookie sheet, spread 3 teaspoons dough in 3 1/2-inch circle, 2 1/2 inches apart. Press in M&M's.
Bake at 350°.

title: wine vinegar dressing
directions: Mix in blender or shake in quart jar.
Can be used on tossed salads.

title: crab dip
directions: Cover cream cheese with crab meat; top with cocktail sauce. Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: potato salad(lyndsey's favorite)
directions: While cubed potatoes cook until tender, chop the celery, onion, carrot and pickle and place into mixing bowl. Toss to mix flavors. Drain potatoes. Rinse to cool down; drain.
Add to vegetables. Fold in mustard, eggs, mayo, salt and pepper. Take care not to squash up
the potato cubes. Chill and enjoy.

title: hamburgers
directions: Mix
soup mix with hamburger very thoroughly with fork. Soak bread in a bowl of milk; squeeze most of the milk out of bread. Break
into
small	pieces.
Add to hamburger mixture. Add chopped
onion
and
mix
again.
Add
eggs and whip into hamburger
mixture	with fork until completely blended.
Don't worry
about
mashing
up the hamburger; mix thoroughly.
Now, add milk
a
little at a time, until the mixture is tacky and sticks slightly
to
fingers
when
forming
patties.
Fry in butter over high heat
until brown on both sides.
Reduce heat and cook until done.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; cream oleo and sugar until light.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Form into a roll and wrap in wax paper. Chill thoroughly and cut with sawing motion into very thin slices.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter and microwave for 1 minutes and 45 seconds on High, then add vanilla and nuts.
Stir and microwave for 1 minute. Put mixture in a greased 8-inch pan. Refrigerate until set.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: This recipe makes about 120 sticks.

title: meatballs
directions: Make spaghetti sauce per your favorite recipe.
Form mixture of ingredients into balls.
Bake at 300° until done (20 to 30 minutes).
Remove meatballs from oven and heat meatballs in sauce for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix and bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Beat the eggs slightly.
Add sugar, oil and pumpkin, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 40 minutes in small loaf pans, 1 hour and 10 minutes if using large loaf pans.

title: brownies
directions: First, put Crisco and chocolate in microwave-safe bowl.
Put in microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Mix all ingredients as listed; add Crisco and chocolate last.
Use an 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine, mixing until well blended. Add flour and mix well.
Chill.
Divide dough into quarters. Divide each quarter into 12 balls.
Press each ball onto bottom and sides of miniature muffin pans.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add cheese, melted butter and other ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown.
Makes great appetizers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Makes two loaves.
Put in greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon bits; sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Chill and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in pieces and cook in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and mash squash.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and bake in 1-quart greased casserole dish for 30 minutes at 400°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry nut bread(blender recipe)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and soda into bowl and set aside. Put egg, shortening, salt, orange rind or grated peel, sugar and orange juice in blender in order listed.
Process until rind is grated fine or until all blended well.
Add nuts and cranberries to blender and process only until nuts and berries are chopped.
Pour over flour mixture and stir only until blended.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use deep-dish pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: fish batter(like long john silvers)
directions: Put flour and salt in a bowl and make a well.
Put egg yolk in center.
Add water and oil to flour and egg yolk mixture.
Mix well; beat egg whites until stiff.
Add to batter and mix well. Roll fish in batter and deep fry 4 to 6 minutes.

title: santa fe pot roast
directions: Combine chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Make small slits in roast; in each slit insert some of the spice mixture.
Add shortening to a Dutch oven; place over medium high heat.
Add roast and brown on all sides.
Add stewed tomatoes, chilies and olives.
Cover and roast in preheated 350° oven for 2 hours or until tender.
Remove roast to serving platter.
Slice.
Drain off liquid and serve in a separate container.
Garnish roast with cilantro.

title: preacher cookies 2
directions: Combine in saucepan the sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk. Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper until cool.

title: millionaires candy
directions: Melt caramels, butter and water in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans; spoon onto waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each. Blend in vanilla and chocolate.

title: creamy potato-carrot soup
directions: In round 2-quart microwave-safe casserole with lid, microwave margarine on High 1 minute.
Stir in onion.
Microwave covered on High 6 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in chicken broth and milk. Using a wire whisk or fork, beat in mashed potatoes, carrots, dried dill weed and pepper.
Cover and microwave on High 6 minutes until hot.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: chicken-rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on box.
Chop onion, eggs, pepper and chicken.
Add all but last three ingredients together, then mix with oil and vinegar.
Add mayonnaise to taste, also salt and pepper.

title: dill sauce for vegetables
directions: Blend until creamy.
Pour over hot vegetables.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all until smooth. Serve with fruit. Can tint with food coloring.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven and add onion and garlic.
Saute until transparent.
Add
meat
and stir to break up meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
This recipe can cook for 3 hours with water	but if	you're	in a hurry, use only 1 cup water and 2 small
cans
of tomato sauce.
Chili will be ready as soon as meat
thoroughly cooks. Time of preparation:
20 minutes to 3 hours.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all but the last 3 ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Top with chips, cheese and almonds.
Let stand (covered) in refrigerator for at least 12 hours.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 well-greased and sugared loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Allow to cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: 20 minute chicken parmesan
directions: Flatten the chicken to an even thickness.
Dip chicken in egg, coat with crumbs.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Crumble in margarine with fingers. Add raisins and caraway seed.
Beat egg and milk together.
Add to dry mixture, retaining 1 teaspoon.
Makes stiff dough.
Roll out and put in a round pan.
Make at cross on top and brush with leftover egg mix.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
For 3 small loaves, bake 1/2 hour.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: In a stockpot, cook pot roast in boiling water for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Drain; reserve 4 cups of liquid.
Cool roast slightly; shred meat with a fork.
Return reserved liquid to stockpot; add hash brown potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, simmer 15 minutes.
Add shredded pork, tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 1 hour.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and 1/3 to 1/2 jar water.
Set aside.
Mix cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg and spices.
Spread 1 1/2 cups meat sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay 4 to 5 noodles on sauce.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese filling on top and 1 cup Mozzarella.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining meat sauce.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and vent one corner.
Microwave on High 10 minutes.
Rotate 1/2 turn.
Microwave on Medium until noodles are tender (approximately 25 minutes). Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in the butter, sugar, flour, pineapple and coconut,
mixing well.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into a loaf and bake, covered, in a shallow pan at 325° for 3 hours.

title: cranberry whipped cream salad
directions: Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Bring to boil; add to Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce and orange rind.
Chill until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and Cool Whip.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add lemon juice and frozen strawberries. Let stand until it starts to thicken. Beat egg whites and add the sugar. Fold the strawberry mixture into the egg whites and pour into a baked pie shell. Top with whipped cream.

title: dairy dinner
directions: Combine everything in a casserole dish and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: no bother biscuits
directions: Stir mayonnaise and milk together.
Mix in flour.
Drop onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 14 to 16 biscuits.

title: carrot pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine with pumpkin, eggs and vanilla. Stir in carrots and raisins.
Spray muffin pans with oil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: two bean chili(serves 6)
directions: Rinse and drain beans.
Melt butter in a large heavy saucepan or Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add onions and garlic and saute until almost golden, about 8 minutes.
Remove from pan and add the ground beef and cook until brown, breaking beef up, about 10 minutes.
Stir in chili powder, cumin and cayenne and continue cooking for 3 minutes.
Return onion and garlic to pan; add tomatoes with juice, broth, potatoes, carrots, bell pepper and chili sauce.
Cover; simmer until vegetables are tender, about 1 hour.
Stir in beans; simmer until beans are heated through and vegetables are very tender, about 30 minutes.

title: nana's butterball cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in a bowl of confectioners sugar a couple of times to coat balls.

title: real bread and butter pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut bread into cubes.
Heat the milk, sugar and margarine until steaming.
Remove from heat and stir in the vanilla.
Add raisins and nutmeg and/or cinnamon.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs; pour the mixture over the bread.
Mix lightly; add applesauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until top is brown. Serve warm with whipped topping, ice cream or rum sauce.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine crackers, margarine and nuts.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Beat pudding and milk well with mixer.
Stir in softened ice cream.
Mix both mixtures together and fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup of crumbs on top and freeze.

title: dilled pasta crab salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package without salt or oil and drain.
Rinse in cold water and set aside.
Gently squeeze out excess water by placing in a colander or strainer.
Drain defrosted peas.
In a large bowl, mix the mayonnaise together with the remaining ingredients.
Add the pasta, crab meat and peas. Adjust seasonings to taste.
Chill.

title: blueberry bangor squares
directions: Blend butter, flour and brown sugar and press into an 9 x 12 inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over the hot crust. Bake about 20 minutes longer at 375°.
Serve in squares.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together the Veg-All, soup, celery, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and cheese in a greased casserole.
Top with the crackers, which have been mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: golden herbed onions
directions: Place onion rings in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter in medium size saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour; slowly stir in evaporated milk and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add parsley, salt, marjoram, pepper and shredded cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted and sauce is smooth.
Pour cheese sauce over onions in casserole. Bake in preheated oven at 350° until onions are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and mash them.
Pour in eggs; add 1/4 cup of brown sugar and 1/4 cup melted butter with cinnamon and orange juice.
Mix well.
Put in glass baking dish; smooth top.
Top with pecans, 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Excellent with turkey and gravy.

title: skillet oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa in skillet.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop on wax paper with a teaspoon.

title: carrot-teen soup(for all ages)
directions: Bring 1/3 of tomato juice to simmer.
Add cut up onions to cook with herbs and pepper while cleaning and cutting carrots. Add carrots to tomato juice that is cooking and add remainder of tomato juice.
If you wish, add red kidney beans next day or later.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in a baking dish (grease good).
Bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes.
The last 30 minutes, remove from oven and crumble 2 cups corn flakes and melted butter. Spread on top of casserole.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, break into bits.
Saute onion in some of the grease.
Mix all.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or add 1/4 cup more gingersnaps and microwave on High 10 minutes.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender. Drain. Combine noodles, cooked chicken, mayonnaise and vegetables. Blend soup and milk. Heat through. Add cheese. Heat and stir until cheese melts. Add to noodle mixture. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 425° about 20 minutes. Sprinkle fried onions over top. Cook another 5 to 8 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until almost done.
Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients except macaroni and mix.
Simmer to heat.
Mix with macaroni and put in baking dish.
Top with sliced Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese melts at 350°.

title: chocolate cream
directions: Beat the egg yolks well; add them to the grated chocolate, sugar and 1 pint of the cream.
Stir well.
Pour ingredients into a basin; set the basin into a saucepan (double boiler) of boiling water.
Stir it one way until the mixture thickens, but do not allow it to boil, or it will curdle.
Strain the cream through a sieve into a basin.
Stir in the gelatin and the other 1/2 pint of cream, which should be well whipped.
Mix all well together; pour it into a mold which has been previously oiled with the purest salad oil.
Set the mold in ice; chill until ready to serve.

title: turkey biscuit stew
directions: Melt margarine.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add turkey broth and milk; cook until thick.
Add turkey, onion, peas and carrots. Simmer until bubbly.
Place this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and put biscuits on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Can cut recipe in half, if desired.
This is good eating.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter baking dish. Add chicken, then layer the cheese over the chicken.
Mix stuffing with seasoning that comes with it and 1 stick margarine.
Put on top of cheese.
Mix the soup and milk. Pour over top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops and set aside.
Combine soup, milk and sour cream.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/2 cup of French fried onions.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange pork chops over potato mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, 1
1/3 cup water, 1/2 cup peanut butter and oil, blending well.
Pour batter onto greased 9 inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees or until cakes tests done. Cool.

title: 1-2-3 beef stew
directions: Put in a large covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours. Add a little sherry before serving (optional).
Serve over noodles.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well with electric mixer.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pie shells at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 300° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.

title: easy grilled chicken
directions: Prick chicken with fork.
Pour dressing over chicken and marinate overnight.
Grill.

title: oatmeal bread *
directions: Bring water to boil; pour over oats.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with oat mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion and celery until tender in 4 tablespoons butter. Add flour and blend with broth, milk and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until thickens some.
Add broccoli, mushrooms, meat and cheese.
Heat and serve.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine in skillet.
Add broccoli and stir until broccoli is soft.
Add rice.
Add Cheez Whiz and dry mustard or Worcestershire to taste; stir again.
Pour into baking dish. Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves about 8.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg, milk and butter together; add to flour mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Drop 6 to 8 dumplings from tablespoon into hot broth.
Cover tight and return to boiling.
Reduce heat; don't lift cover.
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cabbage in a pan
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add cabbage; cover to hold in steam.
Cook on low to moderate heat (about 8 minutes) until tender.
Season to taste, adding crumbled bacon if you like.

title: coconut-chocolate logs
directions: Melt chocolate chips with milk over hot water; remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt and confectioners sugar.
Chill mixture until firm enough to shape, approximately 1 hour.
Place half of mixture between sheets of wax paper and shape into a log.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Now roll logs in coconut until heavily coated.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until ready to slice.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble meat. Drain well.
Combine beef and next 6 ingredients.
Stir well.
Cook in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put bacon on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook carrots and onions until tender.
Cook squash separately until tender.
Put squash, carrots and onion in casserole dish. Spread sour cream and chicken soup on top.
Dot with butter, then cover with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake until cheese is bubbly.

title: summer salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Slice cucumbers and onion.
Dice bell pepper and tomatoes.
Combine all this.
Then mix together mayonnaise and vinegar.
Toss with vegetables and macaroni.
Season to taste. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream with electric mixer. Add cinnamon to taste.
Cut fruit into bite-size pieces.
Apples are especially good with this dip.
Serves 1 1/2 cups.

title: congealed orange-buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple and liquid to a boil on medium heat in a saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin until dissolved. Cool.
Add buttermilk and chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
This can either be spooned into a lightly greased Jello mold or an oblong baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on a lettuce-lined plate or cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.	Delicious!
Serves 10.

title: saucy baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot shortening, season with salt and pepper. Drain off grease.
Combine rest of ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: homestyle bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add butter to milk and scald.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs; add sugars, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in bread cubes and raisins.
Spray 9 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.
Pour bread mixture into dish.
Place dish in pan of hot water (1-inch deep).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm with Lemon Sauce or cream, if desired.

title: roast chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Sprinkle inside cavity of chicken with thyme and salt.

Add 1 teaspoon butter, celery and onion. Rub outside of chicken with remaining butter. Tuck wing tips under back of chicken. Place chicken, breast side down, on rack in roasting pan. Add enough water to cover bottom of pan. Roast for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 375°.
Roast for 20 minutes longer. Turn chicken, breast side up.
Roast until chicken is browned, about 30 minutes longer.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Sift first three ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour gradually. Drop by teaspoon on greased pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer peaches (with syrup), dry cake mix, butter and coconut in ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Bake until topping is golden brown, 55 to 60 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; chop and saute in the oil or butter until moisture is gone.
Combine all ingredients except mushroom caps.
Stuff caps.
Add water to pan to prevent sticking or put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: southern mint julep
directions: You will need 1 (10 ounce) silver julep cup or tall glass.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix well until blended.
If too sticky, add more confectioners sugar.

title: split pea soup
directions: Wash peas and soak overnight in enough water to cover.
In the morning, boil the ham hock in water for 1/2 hour.
Add the peas and soaking water to the ham hock kettle, cover and boil slowly until the peas are mushy, about 1 hour.
Remove the ham hock.
Scrape and slice carrots and add, with onions, to the cooked peas.
Salt if necessary.
Cook for another 30 minutes.
If there is meat on the ham hock, chop fine and return to soup.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Let cool.
Debone and remove skin. Cook Stove Top stuffing as directed.
In a casserole dish, line bottom with layer of stuffing.
Add a layer of chicken and a can of soup, plus a can of chicken broth from cooked chicken.
Repeat steps and end with a layer of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Carefully cut uncooked bacon into small pieces.
Next, dice the onion.
Place uncooked bacon, onion, beans, brown sugar, catsup, mustard and molasses in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix well with a large spoon.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Garnish with cooked bacon, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Spray bowl and ladle with Pam.
Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over Chex; stir well and cool.
Mix together powdered sugar and cocoa.
Put into hand shaker strainer; shake off excess sugar.
Store in covered container, not airtight.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute okra in shortening 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Add onions, garlic, salt, pepper and shrimp. Cook 5 minutes, then add water, tomatoes, bay leaves and pepper sauce. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Remove bay leaves and serve over hot rice.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add to potatoes and veggies.
Mix soup and juice well and pour over mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Sift flour into large bowl.
Beat eggs and add with rest of ingredients to flour.
Mix well, scraping bowl often.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool in pans or on wire rack.
Store in plastic wrap or wrap in freezer paper and freeze.

title: spareribs with onion sauce
directions: Cut ribs in 3 or 4 rib pieces and put in foil lined pan.
Roast at 400° for 20 minutes.
Drain fat.
Saute onions and garlic until onions are limp.
Add vinegar, chili sauce, sugar, marjoram, allspice, mustard and Worcestershire.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour onion sauce over ribs.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° until ribs are tender.
If ribs brown too fast, cover with foil.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat stirring constantly until tender (about 5 minutes).
Combine cooked vegetables, cornbread crumbs and next 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Spoon into a lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 10 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 12 servings.
One 8-inch iron skillet makes 4 cups of crumbs of cornbread.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Combine flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds to soften.
Gradually add the 1 cup sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; beat well. Stir dry ingredients into beaten mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.

title: chicken crescents(kids will love these!)
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, salt, pepper and marjoram until as smooth as possible.
Add chicken.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 triangles and seal perforations.
Spoon chicken mixture into center of rectangles, dividing mixture evenly.
Pull corners of dough to center.
Seal corners and perforations again.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Top with crushed stuffing.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Brown your hamburger meat and cook your macaroni and cheese. Mix all ingredients.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Add coconut, raisins and nuts which have been rolled in flour.
Add beaten egg whites last.
Bake in 4 layers at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme. Add other ingredients. Chill. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: sheila's lemon breeze
directions: First Layer:
flour, butter, pecans or walnuts.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil in a blender or food processor. Blend mixture until mixed well but still a little chunky. Place 2 to 3 inches of oil in a skillet and heat. Drop teaspoonfuls of the mixture into hot oil and cook for several minutes until golden brown. Place on a paper towel to drain. Serve warm with a variety of sauces including duck sauce, sweet and sour sauce and plum sauce. These little goodies are very tasty. I used a deep fat fryer to cook the shrimp balls but 2 or 3 inches of oil in a skillet should work just as well. Just make sure you keep the oil very hot and only cook one or two at a time.

title: cupcakes
directions: Sift flour 3 times.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each one.
Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time, until all of flour is used.
Add vanilla. Bake in greased muffin tins 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Makes 18 large or 24 small muffins.

title: super easy fudge
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 pan. Heat milk and chips over low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat. Quickly stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread in pan. Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until firm.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla and set aside.
Mix the two bowls together.
Crumble half the cookies into bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread creamy mixture on top and add remaining cookies on top.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: bacon yum yums
directions: Place bacon slices in a single layer in a shallow pan (jelly roll pan).
Combine brown sugar and mustard; sprinkle mixture over bacon slices.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Drain; cut into desired pieces with kitchen scissors.
These may be served for a brunch or as an appetizer.

title: nippy pineapple sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Serve warm.
Use as dip for chicken nuggets.
Makes 1 cup.

title: easy  stromboli
directions: Mix pizza crust by direction on pkg. roll out into a 9x14 rectangle. Spread salsa down center, add ham then spices, add cheese, then pepperoni.

title: wassail(christmas punch)
directions: Combine cider and cinnamon stick in a large saucepan and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover and stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: smothered steak
directions: Wet steak and cut in serving pieces. Sprinkle salt, pepper and garlic over both sides of steak and roll in flour. Fry in oil until brown on both sides. About 2 minutes on each side. After all the steak has been browned put it in a baking dish and slice onions over the steak. Set aside.
Pour all but 8 Tbsp drippings from frying pan. Add 1/4 c.

flour to drippings and brown. Add enough water to make a water thin gravy. Pour over steak, cover and bake in 350 degree oven for about an hour. Gravy should cover steak. This will make medium thick gravy.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on back of box.
Poke holes in cake as soon as it comes out of oven (with straw).
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Heat hot fudge sauce; pour over cake.
Cool completely.

title: ripe tomato chili
directions: Chop and mix the first 5 ingredients and let set overnight. The next day, drain chopped mixture and add the next 5 ingredients.
Simmer this mixture for 15 minutes.
Pour into canning jars and put in water bath for 10 minutes.

title: coney island sauce for hot  dogs
directions: Cook ground beef, drain. Add all other ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes. Use on top hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: haley's peanut butter balls
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add other ingredients. Roll into small (marble-sized) balls.
Place on wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Mix well. Dip each ball into chocolate mix.
Place on wax paper to harden. Keep chocolate mixture warmed while dipping.
Yield: 8 dozen. Great idea for gift package.

title: grapenut dessert
directions: Mix Grape-Nuts, bananas, oranges and sugar in a large bowl. Whip cream at medium speed for 2 minutes and fold into mixed ingredients.
Chill and serve!

title: glazed pearl onions
directions: In a deep 12 inch skillet, over high heat, heat 1 inch water to boiling.
Add onions, heat to boiling.
Boil one minute.
Drain. Peel onions, leave a little of the root ends to help hold shape during cooking.
In same skillet, over high heat, heat one inch water to boiling.
Add onions, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5-10 minutes until onions are tender.
Drain. Wipe skillet dry.
In same skillet, over high heat, cook onions, butter or margarine, currant jelly, sugar and salt, stirring occasionally, until onions are browned and glazed, about 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable strata supreme
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange vegetables on the bottom of the dish.
Cut bread slices into 1/2-inch cubes. Sprinkle the vegetables with the bread cubes and chopped ham. Combine eggs, milk, mustard, garlic powder and onion powder; mix well.
Pour the egg mixture over the rest and sprinkle with cheese. Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight. Uncover and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: linguine with tomatoes and basil
directions: Combine tomatoes, Brie, basil, garlic, 1 cup olive oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper in a serving bowl.
Set aside and leave for at least 2 hours at room temperature.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine milk chocolate morsels, margarine and corn syrup in medium saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla extract and add sugar.
Add Rice Krispies, mixing lightly until well coated.
Spread evenly in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Use Pam to grease.
Cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 48 squares.

title: shrimp-asparagus casserole
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales from stalks. Cut asparagus into 2-inch pieces.
Steam in vegetable steamer for 3 minutes.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Arrange asparagus in a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place shrimp over asparagus.
Set aside.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut and pimentos thoroughly and add celery and onion.
Mix thoroughly in large mixing bowl.
Mix sugar, oil and vinegar.
Heat long enough to melt sugar, no longer.
Pour over mixture in mixing bowl.
Chill.

title: triple chocolate brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch pie plate.
In small mixing bowl, beat eggs and blend in sugar and butter.
In separate bowl, stir together the flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to egg mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Spread batter into pie plate.
Bake for 35 minutes, or until set.
Pie will not test done in center.
Cool.
Serve with ice cream and syrup.

title: kupusta - aunt jo's
directions: Cook separately each one.

title: mandarin cream cake
directions: Put cake mix, oil, eggs, oranges and juice into mixer bowl. Mix until smooth, but no longer.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes or until cake tests done (don't overcook).
Cool thoroughly before icing.

title: marinated mozzarella and artichoke hearts
directions: One and a half hours before serving:
In large bowl mix cheese, artichoke hearts and their marinade, red pepper pieces, rosemary, crushed red peppers and salt.
Cover mixture with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors.

title: d b's hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well and put into a 9x13 casserole. Top with bread crumbs. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
This is a hearty, satisfying, and unusual morning dish which would also be good for brunch or dinner.

title: mighty muffins
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine bran and milk; let stand for 3 minutes.
Stir in egg, molasses and butter or margarine; set aside.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, wheat germ, baking powder and baking soda.
Make a well in the center.
Add bran mixture; stir until moistened.
Fold in raisins and nuts.

title: easy no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pack into loaf cake pan or pans sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 days before slicing.

title: heavenly orange fluff(serves 12)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and concentrate.
Add oranges and chill until firm.
Beat pudding and milk with rotary beater until smooth; fold in Cool Whip. Spread over top.

title: turnip roots
directions: Slice turnips 1/4-inch thick.
Combine turnips, water, salt, pepper, sugar and salt pork in a heavy pot.
Cover and cook on high heat for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium low and cook for thirty minutes or until tender.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: In the bottom of 9x13 inch pan, place one layer of graham crackers.
Mix vanilla pudding with 3 cups milk.
Combine this with cool whip.
Spread half of the mixture on the layer of crackers.
Put another layer of crackers on top of this.
Top with remaining pudding mixture.
Add another layer of crackers.
Mix frosting with 3 tbsp. of milk until it is spreading consistency. Spread the frosting over the top layer of crackers.
Refrigerate 12-24 hours.
May be frozen.

title: snow peas and water chestnuts
directions: In oil pan or wok, heat oil; add vegetables.
Cook until tender; add sugar and broth.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Melt chocolate chips with butter in top of double boiler. Combine nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in waxed paper lined 9x13 pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Remove from pan. Peel off wax paper.
Cut into squares.
Cover and store at room temperature.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark over double boiler.
Melt in chips.
Stir in peanuts.
Spoon on wax paper and cool.

title: easy layered beef enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Cook ground beef, onions, and garlic until thoroughly cooked. Drain. Add green chiles, salt, and pepper. Mix well. Remove from heat. Pour 1 can enchilada sauce in ungreased 13 x 9 inch glass baking dish. Arrange 4 tortillas in dish overlapping slightly. Spoon beef mixture evenly over tortillas, top with remaining tortillas. Pour remaining can of enchilada sauce over top. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Serve with sour cream if desired.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cut or slice cabbage.
Put in casserole or pan, spread potato soup on top.
Cover and bake one hour or until tender.
Cut up cheese and spread on top.
Cover with onion rings and bake 15 minutes.
Casserole or pan depends on size of cabbage.

title: bea's peach treat
directions: Fill Collins glass with ice.
Blend the brandy and orange juice and strain.
Add the champagne. Garnish with peach slice.

title: brownie peanut butter cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups.
In large bowl, combine brownie mix, water, oil and egg; beat 50 strokes with spoon.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full. Press peanut butter cup into batter until top edge of candy is even with batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until brownie is set.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely.
Makes 12 cupcakes.

title: spinach meat loaf
directions: Defrost frozen spinach and squeeze out excess water with paper towels.
Mix ground beef and bread crumbs together.
Beat eggs together and add to ground beef mixture; mix well.
Add bell pepper, onion, garlic, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper to ground beef mixture, mixing well.
Put ground beef mixture in a 10 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Flatten out meat loaf mixture and add spinach to center, spreading out lengthwise.
Close
up meat loaf by wrapping meat mixture around spinach securely.
Spread mushroom soup over top of meat loaf.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for approximately 1 to
1 1/4 hours.

title: lapa sata
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until meat is done.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese and tortillas) and simmer 15 minutes.
Tear tortillas in pieces.
In a buttered dish, layer tortillas, meat mixture and cheese, ending with cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven until cheese melts and mixture is bubbly.

title: chicken wiggle
directions: Boil hen with onion, celery, salt and pepper to taste.
When done, remove meat from bone.
Save stock.
Cook noodles in broth as directed on package.
Add peas, and mushrooms (cut up); add eggs (cut up) and add chicken.
Sprinkle in garlic salt.
Heat in double boiler as it burns easy.
Tastes better if made a day ahead.

title: 90-minute dinner rolls
directions: Combine 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and butter until liquids are 120° to 130°.
Add to dry ingredients; beat for 2 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured board; knead 2 to 3 minutes until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; grease top.
Cover.
Place bowl into large pan of very warm water (about 120°).
Let rise 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add oil, eggs and sugar.
Beat until smooth and well mixed.
Add apples, vanilla, cinnamon and pecans.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Add milk, chopped pecans and crushed pineapple to the cream cheese.
Mix and prepare Dream Whip according to box directions. Add sugar to it.
Mix these 2 mixtures together and pour into baked pie shells.
Refrigerate.

title: chess cake
directions: Combine ingredients with a mixer.
Mash down in 9 x 13-inch pan (packing tightly).

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll or absorb moisture on paper towels.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, roll ball in chopped pecans.
Put on Ritz crackers.

title: crock-pot boston brown bread
directions: Stir together flours, cornmeal, baking powder, soda and salt. Combine egg, molasses, sugar and oil. Add flour mixture to molasses mixture alternately with buttermilk; beat well. Stir in raisins. Turn batter into 2 well-greased 16-ounce vegetable cans. Cover cans tightly with foil. Place cans in crockery cooker. Cover and cook on high heat setting for 3 hours. Remove cans from cooker. Cool 10 minutes in cans. Serve warm. Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate truffle buns(makes 20)
directions: Whisk together the eggs and sugar until very thick and pale. Heat the milk, butter and vanilla essence until almost boiling. Very slowly, whisk the hot milk into eggs.
Sift together the flour and salt and fold into the egg mixture.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix confectioners sugar with cream cheese, margarine and vanilla.
Spread on unrolled cake.
Reroll and refrigerate.
Slice as you serve.

title: spinach kugel
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Beat eggs by hand and add other ingredients; then fold in noodles.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Serves 15.

title: cola salad
directions: Mix juices from cans of fruit with amount of water called for, hot water.
Bring to boil.
Turn off fire add Jell-O and dissolve. Add Jell-O, fruits and nuts.
Add the Coke slowly so it doesn't fizz too bad.
Add rest of water (leave out about 1/2 cup so it will jell better and will be firmer).
Add smushed cream cheese. Cool.
Stir now and then.

title: tiny t's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except parsley and paprika.
Chill.
Form into a ball.
Roll in parsley flakes and paprika.

title: tuna cheese melts(low-fat)
directions: In small bowl, combine tuna, celery, onion, salad dressing and lemon pepper seasoning; mix well.
Spread about 1/4 cup tuna mixture on each slice of toast.
Place on broiler pan or ungreased cookie sheet.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until tuna mixture is hot.
Top each with cheese slice; broil an additional 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn and peppers. Pour 1/2 of the batter into greased pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the corn and peppers over the batter.
Pour remaining batter, corn and peppers into pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mrs. myrtle's barbecue sauce
directions: Whisk altogether.
Great on chicken, beef, pork or venison.

title: mrs. mulligan's irish bread
directions: Sift first 4 dry ingredients together.
Mix in butter or shortening.
Put in raisins.
Beat egg in cup with fork; add milk. Add to mixed ingredients.
Bake in greased bread pan at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.
If buttermilk is used in place of sweet milk, add speck of baking soda.

title: sherry pound cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Place pecans in bottom.
Beat other ingredients together and pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Make holes in cake with toothpick. Add half of hot glaze while in pan.
Set 30 minutes.
Turn out and put remaining glaze on cake.

title: oriental salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender or by hand with a whisk.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
Use on chicken or tuna salad.

title: lemon pies
directions: Mix all together.
Put in graham cracker pie crust.
Chill until firm.
Can double ingredients.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix together in a big bowl, using 2 1/2 cups milk.
Add remaining 1/4 cup, if needed.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, separate every slice of bread and saturate with milk.
Let stand until soggy.
Cut or mash soggy bread into bite-sizes.
Add salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, sugars and egg.
Mix well and stir in raisins.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake for 30 minutes.
If consistency is too moist or sticky, return to oven and check every 5 to 10 minutes until baked to desired consistency.
Serve hot with cold milk and butter on top. Microwaves well.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for a minimum of 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 salads.
Good as a light meal served with rolls and fruit for dessert.

title: warm coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onions, celery seed and salt; set aside.
In small skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; crumble over cabbage.
Remove most drippings from skillet, leaving about 1 tablespoon.
Add sugar, vinegar and paprika; heat until sugar dissolves.
Pour warm dressing over cabbage and toss.
Serve immediately.

title: florida-style vegetable dip
directions: Blend with hand mixer and chill.
Use small curd cottage cheese.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Lightly brown hamburger in skillet. Add onions and cook until tender. Stir in sauce, water and seasonings. Simmer 25 minutes. Place half of spaghetti in a 2-quart casserole. Cover with half of sauce. Sprinkle half of cheese on sauce; repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: amanda's ugly dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with 3/4 bottle of dressing.
Let stand overnight.
Before serving mix in remaining dressing.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in order given.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream. Best when cooled first.

title: baked apples and cinnamon
directions: Place ingredients in a microwave-safe bowl.
Cover and microwave on high for 4 minutes.
Stir, and continue microwaving for another 4 minutes.
Stir again.
Apples should be fork tender. If necessary microwave on high for an additional 2 minutes. Serve as a topping over low-fat ice cream or frozen yogurt or eat alone.

title: venison jerky
directions: Cut meat across the grain into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Put in large bowl.
Mix sauces and spices and marinate meat overnight (12 hours).

title: lo-cal mocha jello
directions: Mix cocoa and water.
Bring to boil and cook 2 minutes; cool. Add more water, if necessary, to make 1/2 cup.
Sprinkle gelatin over this to soften.
Add Sweet 'N Low and hot coffee.
Mix until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into four pretty glasses.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: ham ball
directions: Blend cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Add ham and all other ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Refrigerate until firm (overnight).
Roll into ball or place in small dish.
Cover with chopped pecans.
Serve with fancy crackers.

title: praline confection
directions: Line 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with graham crackers. Bring butter and sugar to rolling boil in medium saucepan.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
When bubbling has stopped, add nuts.
Spoon over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Yields 40 squares.

title: texas barbecue
directions: Place brisket in large glass baking dish.
Sprinkle meat with tenderizer.
Combine all remaining ingredients except Barbecue Sauce and rub on meat.
Cover and refrigerate the brisket overnight.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours, covered.
Add water if liquid is needed.
Pour Texas Barbecue Sauce over brisket and cook 1 hour longer.
Let stand for 15 minutes, then slice thinly across the grain.

title: red snapper bake
directions: Place fillets in large buttered baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of lemon juice and dot with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: macadamia fantastics
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add chocolate and white chips; add nuts last.
Make size of golf balls, using an ice cream dipper.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° until light brown.

title: old english toffee
directions: Combine ingredients. Cook until 294°.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Cool.
Spread with melted chocolate and sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: chicken waldorf
directions: Drain pineapple well; reserve 1/4 cup juice.
Chop chicken breast.
In large bowl, combine chicken, pineapple juice, poppy seed, vanilla and lemon peel.
Pour over chicken mixture and toss well.
Put on lettuce and serve with French bread.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda and set aside.
Use an electric mixer to cream butter.
Add vanilla and sugars and beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg.
At low speed beat in cocoa, then add milk. With a wooden spoon mix in dry ingredients just until blended. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.

title: delicious apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 6-cup baking dish or 10-inch pie plate.
Mix apples with cinnamon, nutmeg, lemon juice, walnuts, raisins and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread in baking dish. Combine remaining sugar with flour in a bowl.
Cut in margarine or butter with pastry blender or two knives until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Spread over apples.
Bake until top is lightly browned, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream or whipping cream if dairy, but it is plenty sweet without it.

title: cashew nut casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and onion.
Add seasonings. Cook noodles in boiling water.
Combine soup and milk.
Stir in noodles.
Add mushrooms, olives, cheese and seasoned beef.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir in chow mein noodles and cashews.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: rae's pie crust
directions: Cut together first 3 ingredients with a pastry blender.
Mix, in a one-cup measure, egg with vinegar.
Fill the cup with milk. Mix together.
Put mixture in refrigerator a few minutes before rolling.
Sprinkle Carnation milk on crust, if desired.

title: crisp squash-pepper toss(microwave)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add squash and cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add onion, garlic, pepper and olive oil.
Toss gently. Microwave 2 to 4 minutes and add kielbasa.
Toss.
Cover and microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Set aside.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Alternate additions of dry ingredients with pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.

Stir in chocolate chips or raisins. Drop 1/4 cup dough onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until cookies are firm and lightly browned. Remove from sheet and cool on racks. (For smaller cookies, decrease cooking time.)
Yields approximately 20 cookies, maybe 24!

title: stewed squash
directions: Chop squash; combine with onion and oil in a skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons water, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often.
Turn to low heat after mixture is slightly tender.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: paw-print cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend sugars, peanut butter, magarine, egg and vanilla until creamy.
Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder into creamed mixture.
Stir until flour is blended.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll into cocoa.
Place balls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from oven and immediately use your little finger to make the paw print.
Cool on rack.
