title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and pour into an 8-inch square baking dish.

title: quick spaghetti
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet and lightly brown meat.
Add onion, garlic, oregano, bay leaf, basil, savory, nutmeg and light brown sugar; simmer 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste and simmer, stirring now and then for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste and slowly cook 5 minutes more.
Serve sauce over spaghetti cooked by package directions and well drained.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer.
Works well on low in crock-pot.

title: fastelavens boller
directions: Mix together in a bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Mix together the yeast and warm water. Set aside.
Heat margarine and milk to lukewarm.
Melt margarine.
Scramble 1 egg
and add a little of the margarine/milk mixture to the egg.
Pour the yeast into the dry ingredients, then add the rest of the liquids and stir well. I use my Kitchen Aid to knead the dough for a few minutes.
Let the dough set with a towel over it for about 1 hour.
Roll out into buns and let rise again about 45 minutes before baking.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk.
Boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream and chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add nuts and blend well.
Pour into a large, greased dish. Cool and slice.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix the molasses with the buttermilk. Add molasses mixture alternately with the flour to the creamed sugar and butter.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by teaspoon approximately 1 inch apart onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop squash and cook in salted water until tender.
Add soup, onion and sour cream.
Melt butter in pan and stir in stuffing mix. Place a layer of the buttered stuffing mix in a casserole dish. Add the squash and top with another layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nanie's meat soup
directions: Fill pot with water.
Cover meat; add meat bones.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add split pea soup mix, barley, lima beans, carrots, chicken bouillon, celery, salt and baking soda.
Cook for 2 to 4 hours.
Add potatoes in last 1 1/2 hours of cooking.
It's a meal! My mom's recipe.

title: ground turkey spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground turkey, bell peppers and onions over medium heat. Drain liquid.
Heat tomato sauce on low heat and stir.
Add ground turkey mixture to tomato sauce.
Add garlic cloves, oregano, soy sauce, mushrooms, steak sauce and peeled tomatoes to sauce.
Season to taste with garlic powder and onion powder.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, white syrup and peanuts together until peanuts are turning slightly brown (can be cooked too long), stirring constantly.
Take off stove and add soda; stir like crazy.
Pour onto well buttered cookie sheet.
Do not smooth out.
Cool quickly in a cold room or area.
Break into pieces.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Make syrup of water, sugar, oleo and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil. Put cut sweet potatoes in boiling syrup.
Cover and boil slowly until potatoes are done. They should be clear and delicious.

title: bourbon hot dogs (drunken weenies)
directions: Combine bourbon, brown sugar and chili sauce.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add hot dogs and simmer until warmed.
For better results, refrigerate overnight.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate mousse supreme
directions: Melt chips and water in top of double boiler or microwave. Beat egg yolks with sugar; blend in melted chocolate.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture with whipped cream.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 8 sherbet dishes or wine glasses.
Chill 6 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Refrigerate.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Crumble nuts and put in bottom of pan.
Mix cake, pudding, rum, water, oil and eggs.
Mix 2 minutes.
Pour over pecans and bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove and immediately pour hot glaze over cake.

title: moist chocolate brownies
directions: In a small saucepan, melt Crisco and butter.
Remove from heat.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar until fluffy. Add cocoa, vanilla and Crisco and butter mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in flour.
Pour batter into a greased 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from sides of the pan.
Cool in pan before cutting into squares.

title: date pudding
directions: Bring brown sugar, water and butter to a boil.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar, chopped dates, nuts, milk, baking powder and flour together in a bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls into syrup in the cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken with cranberries
directions: Cook chicken one half hour.
Cover with mixture of remaining ingredients.
Cook 1/2 hour longer or until chicken is tender. Bake at 350°.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Combine strawberries with gelatin.
Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan and spread with marshmallows.
Prepare cake mix and pour over marshmallows.
Spoon strawberry mixture over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve upside down with whipped cream.

title: banana apple raisin muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine the rest of the ingredients except raisins.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until mixed well.
Fold in raisins.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, baking in a muffin pan with paper liners one-half filled.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour rice in bottom of pan.
Add chicken soup and water.
Boil chicken until tender.
Place chicken on top of rice, chicken soup and onion soup.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: onions
directions: Slice onions thin.
Put in a large saucepan.
Add butter, sugar and water to almost cover.
Cook until onions are cooked down and liquid is a syrup.
This is very good with steak.
Save syrup to baste chicken and burgers.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Place rhubarb in shell.
Sprinkle with salt and sugar.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 400° until center is firm (approximately 45 minutes).
Cool before serving.

title: hot artichoke seafood dip
directions: Combine ingredients and spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with bread crumbs and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with toast or crackers.

title: tom thumb bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Pat in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes.
Combine the remaining ingredients and spread on baked crust.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cut into bars when cool.

title: steak and italian peppers
directions: Cut steak into 3/8-inch slices. Cut peppers into thin strips. Saute peppers in oil until tender. Add Ragu sauce; simmer 10 minutes. Broil steak slices 3 minutes on each side. Arrange steak on platter. Spoon sauce over steak.

title: mom's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling, over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, simmer 5 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Thin with water, if desired.
Use with chicken, beef or pork or as a zesty alternative to catsup.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meats and drain fat.
Add garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes and bay leaf; simmer for 30 minutes.
Boil lasagne noodles until they are barely flexible (10 to 15 minutes).
Mix cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, eggs and salt and pepper to taste in a large mixing bowl.
Slice or grate the Mozzarella cheese.

title: caramel peanut butter cake
directions: Mix good.
Make 10 layers.
Bake at 350°.
Don't brown layers. (You may use a yellow cake mix that uses oil.)

title: creamed crabmeat
directions: Drain and slice canned or frozen crab.
Reserve a little for garnish.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add green onions and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add milk gradually, stirring until thickened and bubbly. Stir in crab.
Serve over toast or patty shells.
Sprinkle with reserved crab and parsley.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: apple crunch
directions: Cook apples until done.
Stir in 1 cup sugar.
Spread apples in bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Top with dry cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mushroom toppers
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Slice mushrooms thin and saute in butter.
Cube cream cheese and put in skillet; stir until melted. Spread on party rye and broil until lightly browned.
Serves 18.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil. Add to dry ingredients.
Melt a little butter in a hot pan and cook until lightly browned.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla. Add flour and nuts and mix well. Roll in 1/2-inch balls or press into cookie size.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Let cook and roll in powdered sugar again. Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: pepper cheese log
directions: Grate cheese and mix in mixer with cream cheese, pimento and garlic.
Add nuts and mix by hand.
Shape into rolls the size of Ritz cracker or in one large bowl.
Sprinkle heavily with chili powder.
Keep refrigerated.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix in order.
Bake in a 10 inch pie plate at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve as dip for strawberries, pineapple, etc.

title: chicken curry couscous
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix last 3 ingredients together in a bowl, then add to the couscous mixture. Serve warm or cold as a main dish.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: texas light bread
directions: Scald milk and stir in sugar, lard and salt.
Stir until lard is melted.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle in the yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Now add 4 cups of the sifted flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add the remaining 4 cups bit by bit, blending after each addition.
The dough should not be too stiff.
Turn out on a lightly floured board and knead until satin smooth and elastic. Place balls of dough in a greased bowl.
Brush top with melted butter or lard.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (about 80°) until doubled in bulk.
This will take about 1 1/2 hours.

title: almond shortbread squares
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In a mixing bowl combine milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and almonds.
Spread evenly over prepared crust.
Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool. Cut into bars.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 36.

title: microwave corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine for 30 to 45 seconds.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Cook in low round dish with inverted saucer in the center or in a ring mold.
Cook 17 minutes on 80% power or until knife in center comes out clean like a cake.
For one half the recipe use 1 onion.

title: chicken and shrimp egg rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In food processor, combine nuts, bread crumbs, salt, paprika, oregano and peppers; process until nuts are chopped.
Transfer to a plastic bag.
Pour buttermilk into a medium bowl; dip chicken into buttermilk, then add to bag with pecan mixture and shake.
Arrange in pan in a single layer; drizzle with butter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap chestnuts with bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 45 minutes.
Drain or transfer to another pan. Combine sugars and ketchup.
Pour over chestnuts and bake 30 minutes more.

title: world's greatest cookies
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
Mash with fork.
Bake 12 minutes at 325°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together Wesson oil, sugar, red food coloring and eggs. Blend in flour, buttermilk, vanilla and cocoa, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream and cream cheese.
Serve with bite size fruit.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend together oil and sugar.
Add the eggs, vanilla and cinnamon and beat well.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (lightly greased) at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat fondue
directions: In a double boiler (a little water in the bottom, don't let it boil dry), melt cheese in top.
Stir with a wooden spoon.
Add mayonnaise gradually.
When melted in pot, add crabmeat.
When ready, add wine.
If too thick, add more wine.
Serve with fresh French bread.

title: french fries fat-free
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/4's lengthwise.
Place on cookie sheet. Spray with Pam and sprinkle seasoned salt generously.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
For crunchy, broil until browned.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: In a 6-quart pot, cover corned beef with water and boil until tender, approximately 4 hours.
Skim off fat and add carrots, onions and potatoes.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook 30 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions. Drain.
Cook peas according to directions.
Do not drain.

Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat; blend in flour, salt and nutmeg. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in broth and half and half. Bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in sour cream and sherry.
Add spaghetti, peas, chicken and mushrooms. Stir gently. Turn into ungreased 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Boil lasagne 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef and Italian sausage.
Drain.
Add oregano and garlic.
Heat 5 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Heat 15 minutes.
In separate container,
mix Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley and eggs. Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer 1/2 noodles, then 1/2 cheese mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 sauce mix.
Repeat.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Put 1 can cherries in 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 package of dry cake mix. Pour butter over it and top with nuts and coconut. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chow chow
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar in large saucepan until sugar is dissolved, stirring frequently.
Add onions, bell pepper, cucumbers and cabbage.
Mix well.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours on low heat.
Ladle into 9 hot, sterilized 1-pint jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Seal with 2-piece lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Let stand overnight before serving.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; cool.
Add drained pineapple, marshmallows and bananas; chill until firm.
Heat pineapple juice on top of double boiler (or just in pan).
Combine sugar, flour and egg; mix with pineapple juice and cook until thick, stirring until cool, then stir or beat in cream cheese while mixture is hot.
Spread over gelatin.
Makes a lot!

title: chocolate polka-dot party log
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Stir in marshmallows but do not melt.
Add nuts and coconut.
Shape into a log.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill several hours. Slice and serve.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Cut
squash in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Place cut side down in shallow baking pans; add 1 inch water.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.	Drain.

title: dilly bread
directions: Prospectors in the Klondike were known as "sourdoughs" for their main source of food.
Each one kept a pot full of the bubbling yeasts, or even let sourdough ferment in the top of the flour sack, insulated from the cold.
This was used to prepare bread, hot cakes and the rare waffle, a waffle iron being too heavy to lug on the trail.

title: peach jello delight
directions: Mix one box of Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water. Stir until dissolved. Add ice cream. Stir until creamed. Pour this in 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill until set.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix together cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Add cranberry mixture to gelatin. Mix well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into ball. Chill. When firm, roll in reserved 1/2 cup pecans. Store, covered, in refrigerator. May be reshaped and used again and again.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: glazed onions
directions: Bring a pot of water to a boil.
Add the onions and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain and peel.
Melt the butter in a skillet and stir in the honey.
Add the onions and cook over medium heat, stirring often, for about 10 minutes or until the onions are slightly browned.
Sprinkle with salt and serve.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Soak broccoli in cold water for 15 minutes and drain.
Remove large leaves and tough part of stalks.
Bring chicken broth to a boil over high heat and add broccoli, salt, lemon, green onion, pepper and Tabasco.
Cover pan, lower heat and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes until stalks are tender.
Puree in blender.
In large skillet or pan, melt margarine over medium heat and stir in flour with wire whisk.
When smooth, add puree and continue stirring. When mixture thickens, taste and adjust seasonings.
Warm milk in separate pan and add to broccoli mixture.
When thoroughly mixed, turn off heat.
Serve or can be frozen.
Reheat slowly.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Spoon into a muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Yield:
12 rolls.

title: german baked beans
directions: Brown bacon, then brown hamburger.
Add all other ingredients. Stir well.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles; drain and rinse.
Saute celery and onion in butter and add rest of ingredients with noodles and season with spices.
Mix together.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Put potatoes just covered with cold water in pot and cook until done.
Puree potatoes and liquid.
Set aside in pot.
Saute onions in butter and oil until golden.
Add chopped celery and carrot and cook for 2 minutes.
Add entire skillet contents to the potatoes.
Turn heat to medium and add Parmesan, milk and broth. Stir and cook at a steady simmer for a few minutes or until the fat floating on top disappears.
Add salt to taste.
Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix white
sugar,
brown sugar, shortening, milk, eggs, soda, baking powder
and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheets. Bake at
until light brown.
You can divide the dough into several
different	bowls.	Add
nuts
to one part, chocolate or butterscotch to others as desired.

title: taco soup
directions: Do not drain anything.
Combine all ingredients.

title: red cheese ball
directions: In large bowl, with electric mixer on medium, beat all ingredients except beef.
Shape into ball; wrap in foil and chill. About 30 minutes before serving, remove foil; round up ball with hands, then roll lightly in beef until completely coated.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 1 (3-inch) ball.

title: caramels
directions: Put 1 cup 1/2 and 1/2 milk in with all other ingredients.
Use a large pan (I use Dutch oven).
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add rest of 1/2 and 1/2.*
Cook to soft ball stage on candy thermometer.**
Stir constantly.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
(Sprinkle pan with chopped nuts first, if you want nuts.) Use metal spatula to pry candy out of pan after it has cooled.
Cut candy into small squares and individually wrap in pieces of wax paper.
Makes approximately 100 caramels.

title: apple dolly cake
directions: Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookie dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Slice one package cookies and pat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cheese filling on cookies.
Slice 2nd pack of cookies and place on top of filling.
Bake at 350° until done or until golden brown.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine crab, celery, onion and pimento in bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and lemon juice; toss to mix.
Add just enough mayonnaise to moisten; mix well.
Spoon onto bed of lettuce and sprinkle with parsley.
Garnish with cucumber, tomato or egg slices.
Serve with additional mayonnaise on the side.
Delicious as first course or side salad; both kids and adults seem to enjoy this.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat eggs in mixer bowl. Add sweet potatoes, sugar, 6 tablespoons margarine, milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Spoon into buttered 1-quart baking dish. Combine brown sugar, 2 tablespoons margarine and flour in a bowl; mix well.
Sprinkle over casserole. Top with pecans.
Press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey-beef bean casserole
directions: Brown all meat in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Add onion, chopped.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Cook dry beans and macaroni until tender.
Stir all ingredients into 1 pot and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Serve with crackers or garlic toast and green salad.

title: rich vanilla crust
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a medium bowl combine flour, sugar and salt.
Using a pastry blender, cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles cornmeal.
Add egg yolk; combine with pastry blender.

Gradually sprinkle mixture with 1 tablespoon water and vanilla; combine with pastry just until dough can be gathered into a ball, adding an additional 1/2 tablespoon water, if necessary. Press into a 10-inch scalloped tart pan with a removable bottom or a 9-inch pie plate (flute edges).

title: bacon-almond date wraps
directions: Stuff a whole almond into each date.
Slice each bacon strip into thirds.
Wrap the 1/3 slice of bacon around each almond-stuffed date and secure with a toothpick.
Can roll the date in brown sugar before wrapping in bacon (optional).
Place on nonstick cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake until bacon is crispy.
(Broil 5 1/2-inches from heat with electric oven door partially open.)
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: pete's cheese grits
directions: Cook grits as directed on box.
After grits are done, add cheese.

title: 15 or 30 bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Place in kettle.
Cover with water. Add 2 tablespoons salt.
Soak overnight.

title: sunday swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; pound well into the meat. Work in as much as possible.
Place in large skillet or Pyrex baking dish.
Pour sauce over top.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until tender.

title: meat loaf surprise
directions: Make your favorite meat loaf. Put in deep baking dish. Meat loaf should be no more than 3-inches thick. Put soup on top of meat loaf; smooth out. Mix peas and corn together; pat on top of soup. Top with hash browns or tater tots.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Mash yolks; combine with butter. Add salt, pepper, mustard and vinegar.
Add enough mayonnaise to make a creamy mixture.
Refill egg whites and sprinkle paprika on each.
Chill.
Makes 16 halves.
Serve with deviled ham sandwiches.
Most delicious.

title: holiday ham ball
directions: Heat oven.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly; shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until brown.
Remove immediately from pan.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice into baking pan; pour onion soup over rice. Add 1 cup water.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Place over onion soup.
Spread cream of celery or chicken over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325-350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add water as necessary to keep moist.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, walnuts and melted butter
and pat in paper cups.
Next bowl, combine and beat 7 minutes sugar, orange juice and egg white until it forms stiff peaks.
Fold in sour cream.
Freeze and top with whipping cream to serve.

title: cookout burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Grill them. Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: crescent wedding cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add sifted flour.
Mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pinch off small amount.
Roll between hands and lay on ungreased cookie sheet in the shape of a half moon.
Bake at 400° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool for 6 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in 10 x 12-inch pan.
Crush graham crackers.
Mix with oleo to form a crust.
Mix confectioners sugar with 1 stick of oleo and pour over crust.
Drain pineapple and spread over mixture.
Place sliced bananas on top.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with nuts, strawberries, cherries, etc. Refrigerate or freeze until half frozen.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix and freeze ingredients.
Take out and chop up, then pour ginger ale over.
Takes 3 bottles of ginger ale.

title: mini pecan pies
directions: Blend cream cheese and the 1/2 cup of oleo.
Stir in flour. Chill for 1 hour.
Shape dough into 24 (1-inch) balls.
Place in small muffin pans.
Press dough over bottom and grip sides of pans.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Leaving the cauliflower whole, remove the leaves and the woody base.
Wash and cook with just enough salt water to cover the cauliflower for 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain and place in a shallow baking pan.
Mix the mayonnaise and the mustard together and spread over the cauliflower.
Then sprinkle the cheese over it and bake at 350° for 10 minutes, uncovered.
Yields 8 servings.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix rest of ingredients and mix with first ones.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tortellini with tomatoes and herb dressing
directions: Prepare tortellini, following package directions; drain well and place in a large bowl.
Toss with 1/4 cup of olive oil.
Cool to room temperature.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine cream cheese, sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with cherry pie filling. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: penne con i broccoli(pasta with broccoli)
directions: Soak the raisins in lukewarm water to cover until needed. Heat half the oil in a skillet over moderate heat.
Add the onion and saute until translucent.
Add the tomatoes, season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook for 1 hour to reduce the sauce.

title: fudge cupcakes
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Add nuts and set aside.
In large bowl, mix remaining ingredients, then fold in chocolate mixture.
Spoon into paper lined muffin cups.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30-35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: First, make a syrup by bringing 3 tablespoons butter, brown sugar and water to a boil in a saucepan.
When it boils, remove from heat.

title: hawaiian crunch
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix cereal, peanuts, raisins and banana chips in an ungreased jelly roll pan, 15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Heat margarine and honey in 1-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in cinnamon and salt; pour over cereal mix.
Toss until evenly coated.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in popcorn and coconut.
Sprinkle with additional salt.
Store in an airtight container.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together with electric mixer.
Chill.

title: chocolate cream cheese cupcakes
directions: In little cupcake tins, put mixture of last 9 ingredients in bottom.
Mix the first 5 ingredients and add 1 teaspoon of cream cheese mixture in each tin.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix until well blended. Spread in bottom of pie plate.
Layer onions, black olives, pepper and tomato.
Cover and chill 4 hours or more.
Before serving, add lettuce and Cheddar cheese to cover.
Serve with chips or crackers for dipping.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove fat from broth.
Save broth.
Cut boned chicken in bite size pieces.
Cook pepper and onion in margarine.
Add flour and milk; stir until smooth and then add chopped cheese.
Stir until thick.
Combine sauce with chicken, mushrooms and spaghetti.
Pour into baking pan and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian chicken and pasta
directions: Saute garlic, peppers and onion in olive oil until tender. Add tomatoes (break into chunks), sugar, salt, oregano and basil. Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add boneless raw chicken pieces or shrimp (and olives, if desired) during last 15 minutes of cooking. Serve over hot angel hair pasta.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil the squash and onion together; save liquid.
Mix 1/2 cup liquid and
the 1 cup bread crumbs, 1/2 stick margarine and sour cream and put into casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 cup bread crumbs, cheese and 1/2 cup margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, Wesson oil and eggs together, then add flour, soda and
pineapple.
Beat
all
of this together and bake in a sheet pan at about 350°.

title: stone soup(kids' stuff.  read tale of the stone soup.)
directions: Cook Stone Soup about 1 hour until potatoes are tender.

title: church windows
directions: Melt oleo & chocolate chips, cool.
Add marshmallows, nuts & coconut, stir lightly.
Form into a loaf and store in the refrigerator overnight.
I use tinfoil to roll it in a loaf and more nuts to coat it with.	Slice and serve cold.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all together and marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Arrange pork chops in bottom of large skillet; sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: buttercream cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat.
Beat in egg and almond extract.
Blend in flour.
Chill dough for ease in handling.
Roll out dough to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with floured cutters. Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool and decorate with confectioners sugar frosting.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook until forms soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat whites until stiff.
Slowly pour syrup mixture into whites and add nuts. Mix well. Drop on cookie sheet.

title: wild rice-chicken hot dish
directions: Add wild rice to boiling water.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add rice.
Bake covered at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chili queso roll
directions: Cream together cheeses, 1 tablespoon of chili powder, garlic and pepper.
Mix in chopped walnuts.
Shape into one large roll, about 2-inches in diameter.
Roll in the remaining chili powder sprinkled on wax paper.
Wrap in transparent wrap and chill. Slice into rounds and serve with thin crackers.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Mix half and half with eggs in a large bowl.
Season with salt and nutmeg.
Layer cheese and spinach in pie shells.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Spinach can be omitted or tomatoes can be substituted for spinach.

title: dairy potato bake
directions: Stir all ingredients together, except 1/4 cup butter, corn flakes and paprika.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with flakes, butter and paprika.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: dip
directions: Mix well.
Set in refrigerator for an hour.
Put butter on hands and roll mixture into a ball.
One large pack pecans, chopped fine, roll ball into chopped nuts until covered.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and thoroughly mix.
Pour mixture into deep pie crust.
Cook at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Makes 4 pies.

title: stretch your lemonade
directions: Mix packages of Kool-Aid.
Add sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Cut lemons in quarters; squeeze and drop in pitcher and let set overnight.
Lemons become a favorite for kids to eat while drinking their favorite beverage.

title: rice casserole
directions: Stir all together in casserole and bake for 1 1/2 hours in a moderate oven.

title: baby's chicken casserole
directions: Lightly grease bottom of dish with butter.
Add chicken to dish and spread.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and sour cream in separate bowl, then pour over chicken evenly.
Melt butter and add crushed crackers in separate bowl, then stir until blended.
Then crumble cracker mix on top.
When finished, shake poppy seed on top of dish.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add other ingredients. Pour into 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Put vegetables in bottom of greased casserole dish, starting with onions.
Sprinkle with a little salt and pepper.
Spread on top of vegetables 1/2 of the cheese.
Brown ground beef until gray in color.
Spread over cheese.
Spread tomato soup over ground beef.
Bake, covered with lid or loose foil, at 350° for 1 hour. Remove lid or foil.
Spread with other 1/2 of cheese.
Bake 10 or 15 minutes longer.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir flour into sugar.
Add syrup, canned milk and salt.
Beat 2 eggs with fork.
Heat cream cheese in microwave enough to stir into mixture.
Add eggs and stir well.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Brown onions and beef in pan.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Mix corn muffin mix according to directions.
Pour over beef.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Mix in very large bowl.
Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center.
Add eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Stir together.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Use as you wish to make breakfast muffins.
Will keep up to two weeks in refrigerator.
tags: box wheat bran cereal with raisins

title: hot chili
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 3 hours or longer.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and Wesson oil.
Beat eggs and add.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add slowly to egg mixture alternately with carrots and nuts.
Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar, molasses and salt.
Boil over medium heat until it reaches the hard boil stage.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Mixture will triple in size.
Stir quickly to blend and pour over popcorn.
Shape into balls with buttered hands.
Mixture is very hot, work quickly.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute celery, pepper and onion.
Dice chicken to bite size. Cook spaghetti.
Mix all ingredients and bake in casserole dish at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Grated Cheddar cheese can be sprinkled on top of the casserole before baking.
This dish freezes well.

title: hawaiian ham
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until mix is clear and thick; stir constantly.
Place ham in casserole dish. Add onions, green peppers and pineapple.
Pour sauce over all. Bake at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carolyn's quick pie
directions: Combine lemon or lime juice, condensed milk and Cool Whip; beat.
Pour into crust and chill for 2 hours.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Place all ingredients in plastic bag and shake to coat. Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar with cornstarch.
Gradually add water, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and clear.
Slowly add beaten egg yolks.
Add salt and lemon.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and dip chicken into margarine, then roll in crushed croutons. Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or bake for 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken broth and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring.
Boil for 1 minute; stir in chicken and vegetables. Place in pie crust and top with remaining pie crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: self-filling cupcakes
directions: Cream together the cheese and sugar.
Beat in egg and a dash of salt.
Stir in the chocolate chips and set aside.
Prepare cake mix per package directions.
Fill paper cup lined muffin pans 2/3 full. Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful of the cheese mixture into each cupcake. Bake as directed on cake mix.
